47ALIGN_VAR_32(const int16_t, Search::zeroShort[MAX_CU_SIZE]) = { 0 };

49Search::Search()
50{
51 memset(m_rqt, 0, sizeof(m_rqt));
52
53 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
54 {
55 m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[i] = NULL;
56 m_qtTempCbf[i] = NULL;
57 }
58
59 m_numLayers = 0;
60 m_intraPred = NULL;
61 m_intraPredAngs = NULL;
62 m_fencScaled = NULL;
63 m_fencTransposed = NULL;
64 m_tsCoeff = NULL;
65 m_tsResidual = NULL;
66 m_tsRecon = NULL;
67 m_param = NULL;
68 m_slice = NULL;
69 m_frame = NULL;
70 m_maxTUDepth = -1;
71}
72
73bool Search::initSearch(const x265_param& param, ScalingList& scalingList)
74{
75 uint32_t maxLog2CUSize = g_log2Size[param.maxCUSize];
76 m_param = &param;
77 m_bFrameParallel = param.frameNumThreads > 1;
78 m_numLayers = g_log2Size[param.maxCUSize] - 2;
79
80 m_rdCost.setPsyRdScale(param.psyRd);
81 m_rdCost.setSsimRd(param.bSsimRd);
82 m_me.init(param.internalCsp);
83
84 bool ok = m_quant.init(param.psyRdoq, scalingList, m_entropyCoder);
85 if (m_param->noiseReductionIntra || m_param->noiseReductionInter )
86 ok &= m_quant.allocNoiseReduction(param);
87
88 ok &= Predict::allocBuffers(param.internalCsp); /* sets m_hChromaShift & m_vChromaShift */
89
90 /* When frame parallelism is active, only 'refLagPixels' of reference frames will be guaranteed
91 * available for motion reference. See refLagRows in FrameEncoder::compressCTURows() */
92 m_refLagPixels = m_bFrameParallel ? param.searchRange : param.sourceHeight;
93
94 uint32_t sizeL = 1 << (maxLog2CUSize * 2);
95 uint32_t sizeC = sizeL >> (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift);
96 uint32_t numPartitions = 1 << (maxLog2CUSize - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
97
98 m_limitTU = 0;
99 if (m_param->limitTU)
100 {
101 if (m_param->limitTU == 1)
102 m_limitTU = X265_TU_LIMIT_BFS;
103 else if (m_param->limitTU == 2)
104 m_limitTU = X265_TU_LIMIT_DFS;
105 else if (m_param->limitTU == 3)
106 m_limitTU = X265_TU_LIMIT_NEIGH;
107 else if (m_param->limitTU == 4)
108 m_limitTU = X265_TU_LIMIT_DFS + X265_TU_LIMIT_NEIGH;
109 }
110
111 /* these are indexed by qtLayer (log2size - 2) so nominally 0=4x4, 1=8x8, 2=16x16, 3=32x32
112 * the coeffRQT and reconQtYuv are allocated to the max CU size at every depth. The parts
113 * which are reconstructed at each depth are valid. At the end, the transform depth table
114 * is walked and the coeff and recon at the correct depths are collected */
115
116 if (param.internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
117 {
118 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= m_numLayers; i++)
119 {
120 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[0], coeff_t, sizeL + sizeC * 2);
121 m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[1] = m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[0] + sizeL;
122 m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[2] = m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[0] + sizeL + sizeC;
123 ok &= m_rqt[i].reconQtYuv.create(param.maxCUSize, param.internalCsp);
124 ok &= m_rqt[i].resiQtYuv.create(param.maxCUSize, param.internalCsp);
125 }
126 }
127 else
128 {
129 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= m_numLayers; i++)
130 {
131 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[0], coeff_t, sizeL);
132 m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[1] = m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[2] = NULL;
133 ok &= m_rqt[i].reconQtYuv.create(param.maxCUSize, param.internalCsp);
134 ok &= m_rqt[i].resiQtYuv.create(param.maxCUSize, param.internalCsp);
135 }
136 }
137
138 /* the rest of these buffers are indexed per-depth */
139 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= m_param->maxCUDepth; i++)
140 {
141 int cuSize = param.maxCUSize >> i;
142 ok &= m_rqt[i].tmpResiYuv.create(cuSize, param.internalCsp);
143 ok &= m_rqt[i].tmpPredYuv.create(cuSize, param.internalCsp);
144 ok &= m_rqt[i].bidirPredYuv[0].create(cuSize, param.internalCsp);
145 ok &= m_rqt[i].bidirPredYuv[1].create(cuSize, param.internalCsp);
146 }
147
148 if (param.internalCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
149 {
150 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_qtTempCbf[0], uint8_t, numPartitions * 3);
151 m_qtTempCbf[1] = m_qtTempCbf[0] + numPartitions;
152 m_qtTempCbf[2] = m_qtTempCbf[0] + numPartitions * 2;
153 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[0], uint8_t, numPartitions * 3);
154 m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[1] = m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[0] + numPartitions;
155 m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[2] = m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[0] + numPartitions * 2;
156 }
157 else
158 {
159 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_qtTempCbf[0], uint8_t, numPartitions);
160 m_qtTempCbf[1] = m_qtTempCbf[2] = NULL;
161 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[0], uint8_t, numPartitions);
162 m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[1] = m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[2] = NULL;
163 }
164
165 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_intraPred, pixel, (32 * 32) * (33 + 3));
166 m_fencScaled = m_intraPred + 32 * 32;
167 m_fencTransposed = m_fencScaled + 32 * 32;
168 m_intraPredAngs = m_fencTransposed + 32 * 32;
169
170 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_tsCoeff, coeff_t, MAX_TS_SIZE * MAX_TS_SIZE);
171 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_tsResidual, int16_t, MAX_TS_SIZE * MAX_TS_SIZE);
172 CHECKED_MALLOC(m_tsRecon, pixel, MAX_TS_SIZE * MAX_TS_SIZE);
173
174 return ok;
175
176fail:
177 return false;
178}
179
180Search::~Search()
181{
182 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= m_numLayers; i++)
183 {
184 X265_FREE(m_rqt[i].coeffRQT[0]);
185 m_rqt[i].reconQtYuv.destroy();
186 m_rqt[i].resiQtYuv.destroy();
187 }
188
189 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= m_param->maxCUDepth; i++)
190 {
191 m_rqt[i].tmpResiYuv.destroy();
192 m_rqt[i].tmpPredYuv.destroy();
193 m_rqt[i].bidirPredYuv[0].destroy();
194 m_rqt[i].bidirPredYuv[1].destroy();
195 }
196
197 X265_FREE(m_qtTempCbf[0]);
198 X265_FREE(m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[0]);
199 X265_FREE(m_intraPred);
200 X265_FREE(m_tsCoeff);
201 X265_FREE(m_tsResidual);
202 X265_FREE(m_tsRecon);
203}
204
205int Search::setLambdaFromQP(const CUData& ctu, int qp, int lambdaQp)
206{
207 X265_CHECK(qp >= QP_MIN && qp <= QP_MAX_MAX, "QP used for lambda is out of range\n");
208
209 m_me.setQP(qp);
210 m_rdCost.setQP(*m_slice, lambdaQp < 0 ? qp : lambdaQp);
211
212 int quantQP = x265_clip3(QP_MIN, QP_MAX_SPEC, qp);
213 m_quant.setQPforQuant(ctu, quantQP);
214 return quantQP;
215}

217#if CHECKED_BUILD || _DEBUG
218void Search::invalidateContexts(int fromDepth)
219{
220 /* catch reads without previous writes */
221 for (int d = fromDepth; d < NUM_FULL_DEPTH; d++)
222 {
223 m_rqt[d].cur.markInvalid();
224 m_rqt[d].rqtTemp.markInvalid();
225 m_rqt[d].rqtRoot.markInvalid();
226 m_rqt[d].rqtTest.markInvalid();
227 }
228}
229#else
230void Search::invalidateContexts(int) {}
231#endif

233void Search::codeSubdivCbfQTChroma(const CUData& cu, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx)
234{
235 uint32_t subdiv = tuDepth < cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx];
236 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
237
238 if (!(log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift < 2))
239 {
240 uint32_t parentIdx = absPartIdx & (0xFF << (log2TrSize + 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2);
241 if (!tuDepth || cu.getCbf(parentIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth - 1))
242 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cu, absPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, !subdiv);
243 if (!tuDepth || cu.getCbf(parentIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth - 1))
244 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cu, absPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, !subdiv);
245 }
246
247 if (subdiv)
248 {
249 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
250 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
251 codeSubdivCbfQTChroma(cu, tuDepth + 1, absPartIdx);
252 }
253}
254
255void Search::codeCoeffQTChroma(const CUData& cu, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx, TextType ttype)
256{
257 if (!cu.getCbf(absPartIdx, ttype, tuDepth))
258 return;
259
260 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
261
262 if (tuDepth < cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx])
263 {
264 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
265 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
266 codeCoeffQTChroma(cu, tuDepth + 1, absPartIdx, ttype);
267
268 return;
269 }
270
271 uint32_t tuDepthC = tuDepth;
272 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
273
274 if (log2TrSizeC < 2)
275 {
276 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize == 2 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
277 if (absPartIdx & 3)
278 return;
279 log2TrSizeC = 2;
280 tuDepthC--;
281 }
282
283 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
284
285 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I422)
286 {
287 uint32_t shift = (m_csp == X265_CSP_I420) ? 2 : 0;
288 uint32_t coeffOffset = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2 - shift);
289 coeff_t* coeff = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[ttype] + coeffOffset;
290 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeffNxN(cu, coeff, absPartIdx, log2TrSizeC, ttype);
291 }
292 else
293 {
294 uint32_t coeffOffset = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2 - 1);
295 coeff_t* coeff = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[ttype] + coeffOffset;
296 uint32_t subTUSize = 1 << (log2TrSizeC * 2);
297 uint32_t tuNumParts = 2 << ((log2TrSizeC - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2);
298 if (cu.getCbf(absPartIdx, ttype, tuDepth + 1))
299 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeffNxN(cu, coeff, absPartIdx, log2TrSizeC, ttype);
300 if (cu.getCbf(absPartIdx + tuNumParts, ttype, tuDepth + 1))
301 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeffNxN(cu, coeff + subTUSize, absPartIdx + tuNumParts, log2TrSizeC, ttype);
302 }
303}
304
305void Search::codeIntraLumaQT(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx, bool bAllowSplit, Cost& outCost, const uint32_t depthRange[2])
306{
307 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
308 uint32_t fullDepth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
309 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
310 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
311 uint32_t sizeIdx = log2TrSize - 2;
312 bool mightNotSplit = log2TrSize <= depthRange[1];
313 bool mightSplit = (log2TrSize > depthRange[0]) && (bAllowSplit || !mightNotSplit);
314 bool bEnableRDOQ = !!m_param->rdoqLevel;
315
316 /* If maximum RD penalty, force spits at TU size 32x32 if SPS allows TUs of 16x16 */
317 if (m_param->rdPenalty == 2 && m_slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE && log2TrSize == 5 && depthRange[0] <= 4)
318 {
319 mightNotSplit = false;
320 mightSplit = true;
321 }
322
323 Cost fullCost;
324 uint32_t bCBF = 0;
325
326 pixel* reconQt = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
327 uint32_t reconQtStride = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.m_size;
328
329 if (mightNotSplit)
330 {
331 if (mightSplit)
332 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot);
333
334 const pixel* fenc = mode.fencYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
335 pixel* pred = mode.predYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
336 int16_t* residual = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
337 uint32_t stride = mode.fencYuv->m_size;
338
339 // init availability pattern
340 uint32_t lumaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx];
341 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
342 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdx, tuDepth, true, &intraNeighbors);
343 initAdiPattern(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdx, intraNeighbors, lumaPredMode);
344
345 // get prediction signal
346 predIntraLumaAng(lumaPredMode, pred, stride, log2TrSize);
347
348 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(0, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
349 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(tuDepth, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
350
351 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2);
352 coeff_t* coeffY = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[0] + coeffOffsetY;
353
354 // store original entropy coding status
355 if (bEnableRDOQ)
356 m_entropyCoder.estBit(m_entropyCoder.m_estBitsSbac, log2TrSize, true);
357 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].calcresidual[stride % 64 == 0](fenc, pred, residual, stride);
358
359 uint32_t numSig = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, stride, residual, stride, coeffY, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, false);
360 if (numSig)
361 {
362 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, residual, stride, coeffY, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, true, false, numSig);
363 bool reconQtYuvAlign = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, mode.predYuv.m_size) % 64 == 0;
364 bool predAlign = mode.predYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, mode.predYuv.m_size) % 64 == 0;
365 bool residualAlign = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, mode.predYuv.m_size) % 64 == 0;
366 bool bufferAlignCheck = (reconQtStride % 64 == 0) && (stride % 64 == 0) && reconQtYuvAlign && predAlign && residualAlign;
367 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].add_ps[bufferAlignCheck](reconQt, reconQtStride, pred, residual, stride, stride);
368 }
369 else
370 // no coded residual, recon = pred
371 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(reconQt, reconQtStride, pred, stride);
372
373 bCBF = !!numSig << tuDepth;
374 cu.setCbfSubParts(bCBF, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
375 fullCost.distortion = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(reconQt, reconQtStride, fenc, stride);
376
377 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
378 if (!absPartIdx)
379 {
380 if (!cu.m_slice->isIntra())
381 {
382 if (cu.m_slice->m_pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled)
383 m_entropyCoder.codeCUTransquantBypassFlag(cu.m_tqBypass[0]);
384 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
385 m_entropyCoder.codePredMode(cu.m_predMode[0]);
386 }
387
388 m_entropyCoder.codePartSize(cu, 0, cuGeom.depth);
389 }
390 if (cu.m_partSize[0] == SIZE_2Nx2N)
391 {
392 if (!absPartIdx)
393 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirLumaAng(cu, 0, false);
394 }
395 else
396 {
397 uint32_t qNumParts = cuGeom.numPartitions >> 2;
398 if (!tuDepth)
399 {
400 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx)
401 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirLumaAng(cu, qIdx * qNumParts, false);
402 }
403 else if (!(absPartIdx & (qNumParts - 1)))
404 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirLumaAng(cu, absPartIdx, false);
405 }
406 if (log2TrSize != depthRange[0])
407 m_entropyCoder.codeTransformSubdivFlag(0, 5 - log2TrSize);
408
409 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfLuma(!!numSig, tuDepth);
410
411 if (cu.getCbf(absPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth))
412 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeffNxN(cu, coeffY, absPartIdx, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA);
413
414 fullCost.bits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
415
416 if (m_param->rdPenalty && log2TrSize == 5 && m_slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE)
417 fullCost.bits *= 4;
418
419 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
420 {
421 fullCost.energy = m_rdCost.psyCost(sizeIdx, fenc, mode.fencYuv->m_size, reconQt, reconQtStride);
422 fullCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(fullCost.distortion, fullCost.bits, fullCost.energy);
423 }
424 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
425 {
426 fullCost.energy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fenc, stride, reconQt, reconQtStride, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx);
427 fullCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(fullCost.distortion, fullCost.bits, fullCost.energy);
428 }
429 else
430 fullCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(fullCost.distortion, fullCost.bits);
431 }
432 else
433 fullCost.rdcost = MAX_INT64;
434
435 if (mightSplit)
436 {
437 if (mightNotSplit)
438 {
439 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtTest); // save state after full TU encode
440 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot); // prep state of split encode
441 }
442
443 /* code split block */
444 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
445
446 int checkTransformSkip = m_slice->m_pps->bTransformSkipEnabled && (log2TrSize - 1) <= MAX_LOG2_TS_SIZE && !cu.m_tqBypass[0];
447 if (m_param->bEnableTSkipFast)
448 checkTransformSkip &= cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N;
449
450 Cost splitCost;
451 uint32_t cbf = 0;
452 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = absPartIdx; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
453 {
454 if (checkTransformSkip)
455 codeIntraLumaTSkip(mode, cuGeom, tuDepth + 1, qPartIdx, splitCost);
456 else
457 codeIntraLumaQT(mode, cuGeom, tuDepth + 1, qPartIdx, bAllowSplit, splitCost, depthRange);
458
459 cbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth + 1);
460 }
461 cu.m_cbf[0][absPartIdx] |= (cbf << tuDepth);
462
463 if (mightNotSplit && log2TrSize != depthRange[0])
464 {
465 /* If we could have coded this TU depth, include cost of subdiv flag */
466 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
467 m_entropyCoder.codeTransformSubdivFlag(1, 5 - log2TrSize);
468 splitCost.bits += m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
469
470 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
471 splitCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(splitCost.distortion, splitCost.bits, splitCost.energy);
472 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
473 splitCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(splitCost.distortion, splitCost.bits, splitCost.energy);
474 else
475 splitCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(splitCost.distortion, splitCost.bits);
476 }
477
478 if (splitCost.rdcost < fullCost.rdcost)
479 {
480 outCost.rdcost += splitCost.rdcost;
481 outCost.distortion += splitCost.distortion;
482 outCost.bits += splitCost.bits;
483 outCost.energy += splitCost.energy;
484 return;
485 }
486 else
487 {
488 // recover entropy state of full-size TU encode
489 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtTest);
490
491 // recover transform index and Cbf values
492 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(tuDepth, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
493 cu.setCbfSubParts(bCBF, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
494 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(0, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
495 }
496 }
497
498 // set reconstruction for next intra prediction blocks if full TU prediction won
499 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
500 pixel* picReconY = reconPic->getLumaAddr(cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdx);
501 intptr_t picStride = reconPic->m_stride;
502 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(picReconY, picStride, reconQt, reconQtStride);
503
504 outCost.rdcost += fullCost.rdcost;
505 outCost.distortion += fullCost.distortion;
506 outCost.bits += fullCost.bits;
507 outCost.energy += fullCost.energy;
508}
509
510void Search::codeIntraLumaTSkip(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx, Cost& outCost)
511{
512 uint32_t fullDepth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
513 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
514 uint32_t tuSize = 1 << log2TrSize;
515 bool bEnableRDOQ = !!m_param->rdoqLevel;
516
517 X265_CHECK(tuSize <= MAX_TS_SIZE, "transform skip is only possible at 4x4 TUs\n");
518
519 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
520 Yuv* predYuv = &mode.predYuv;
521 const Yuv* fencYuv = mode.fencYuv;
522
523 Cost fullCost;
524 fullCost.rdcost = MAX_INT64;
525 int bTSkip = 0;
526 uint32_t bCBF = 0;
527
528 const pixel* fenc = fencYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
529 pixel* pred = predYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
530 int16_t* residual = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
531 uint32_t stride = fencYuv->m_size;
532 uint32_t sizeIdx = log2TrSize - 2;
533
534 // init availability pattern
535 uint32_t lumaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx];
536 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
537 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdx, tuDepth, true, &intraNeighbors);
538 initAdiPattern(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdx, intraNeighbors, lumaPredMode);
539
540 // get prediction signal
541 predIntraLumaAng(lumaPredMode, pred, stride, log2TrSize);
542
543 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(tuDepth, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
544
545 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
546 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2);
547 coeff_t* coeffY = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[0] + coeffOffsetY;
548 pixel* reconQt = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
549 uint32_t reconQtStride = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.m_size;
550
551 // store original entropy coding status
552 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot);
553
554 if (bEnableRDOQ)
555 m_entropyCoder.estBit(m_entropyCoder.m_estBitsSbac, log2TrSize, true);
556
557 int checkTransformSkip = 1;
558 for (int useTSkip = 0; useTSkip <= checkTransformSkip; useTSkip++)
559 {
560 uint64_t tmpCost;
561 uint32_t tmpEnergy = 0;
562
563 coeff_t* coeff = (useTSkip ? m_tsCoeff : coeffY);
564 pixel* tmpRecon = (useTSkip ? m_tsRecon : reconQt);
565 bool tmpReconAlign = (useTSkip ? 1 : (m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.m_size) % 64 == 0));
566 uint32_t tmpReconStride = (useTSkip ? MAX_TS_SIZE : reconQtStride);
567
568 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].calcresidual[stride % 64 == 0](fenc, pred, residual, stride);
569
570 uint32_t numSig = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, stride, residual, stride, coeff, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, useTSkip);
571 if (numSig)
572 {
573 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, residual, stride, coeff, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, true, useTSkip, numSig);
574 bool residualAlign = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.m_size) % 64 == 0;
575 bool predAlign = predYuv->getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, predYuv->m_size) % 64 == 0;
576 bool bufferAlignCheck = (stride % 64 == 0) && (tmpReconStride % 64 == 0) && tmpReconAlign && residualAlign && predAlign;
577 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].add_ps[bufferAlignCheck](tmpRecon, tmpReconStride, pred, residual, stride, stride);
578 }
579 else if (useTSkip)
580 {
581 /* do not allow tskip if CBF=0, pretend we did not try tskip */
582 checkTransformSkip = 0;
583 break;
584 }
585 else
586 // no residual coded, recon = pred
587 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(tmpRecon, tmpReconStride, pred, stride);
588
589 sse_t tmpDist = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(tmpRecon, tmpReconStride, fenc, stride);
590
591 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(useTSkip, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
592 cu.setCbfSubParts((!!numSig) << tuDepth, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
593
594 if (useTSkip)
595 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot);
596
597 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
598 if (!absPartIdx)
599 {
600 if (!cu.m_slice->isIntra())
601 {
602 if (cu.m_slice->m_pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled)
603 m_entropyCoder.codeCUTransquantBypassFlag(cu.m_tqBypass[0]);
604 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
605 m_entropyCoder.codePredMode(cu.m_predMode[0]);
606 }
607
608 m_entropyCoder.codePartSize(cu, 0, cuGeom.depth);
609 }
610 if (cu.m_partSize[0] == SIZE_2Nx2N)
611 {
612 if (!absPartIdx)
613 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirLumaAng(cu, 0, false);
614 }
615 else
616 {
617 uint32_t qNumParts = cuGeom.numPartitions >> 2;
618 if (!tuDepth)
619 {
620 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx)
621 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirLumaAng(cu, qIdx * qNumParts, false);
622 }
623 else if (!(absPartIdx & (qNumParts - 1)))
624 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirLumaAng(cu, absPartIdx, false);
625 }
626 m_entropyCoder.codeTransformSubdivFlag(0, 5 - log2TrSize);
627
628 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfLuma(!!numSig, tuDepth);
629
630 if (cu.getCbf(absPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth))
631 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeffNxN(cu, coeff, absPartIdx, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA);
632
633 uint32_t tmpBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
634
635 if (!useTSkip)
636 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtTemp);
637
638 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
639 {
640 tmpEnergy = m_rdCost.psyCost(sizeIdx, fenc, fencYuv->m_size, tmpRecon, tmpReconStride);
641 tmpCost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(tmpDist, tmpBits, tmpEnergy);
642 }
643 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
644 {
645 tmpEnergy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fenc, stride, tmpRecon, tmpReconStride, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx);
646 tmpCost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(tmpDist, tmpBits, tmpEnergy);
647 }
648 else
649 tmpCost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(tmpDist, tmpBits);
650
651 if (tmpCost < fullCost.rdcost)
652 {
653 bTSkip = useTSkip;
654 bCBF = !!numSig;
655 fullCost.rdcost = tmpCost;
656 fullCost.distortion = tmpDist;
657 fullCost.bits = tmpBits;
658 fullCost.energy = tmpEnergy;
659 }
660 }
661
662 if (bTSkip)
663 {
664 memcpy(coeffY, m_tsCoeff, sizeof(coeff_t) << (log2TrSize * 2));
665 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(reconQt, reconQtStride, m_tsRecon, tuSize);
666 }
667 else if (checkTransformSkip)
668 {
669 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(0, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
670 cu.setCbfSubParts(bCBF << tuDepth, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
671 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtTemp);
672 }
673
674 // set reconstruction for next intra prediction blocks
675 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
676 pixel* picReconY = reconPic->getLumaAddr(cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdx);
677 intptr_t picStride = reconPic->m_stride;
678 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(picReconY, picStride, reconQt, reconQtStride);
679
680 outCost.rdcost += fullCost.rdcost;
681 outCost.distortion += fullCost.distortion;
682 outCost.bits += fullCost.bits;
683 outCost.energy += fullCost.energy;
684}
685
686/* fast luma intra residual generation. Only perform the minimum number of TU splits required by the CU size */
687void Search::residualTransformQuantIntra(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth, const uint32_t depthRange[2])
688{
689 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
690 uint32_t fullDepth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
691 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
692 bool bCheckFull = log2TrSize <= depthRange[1];
693
694 X265_CHECK(m_slice->m_sliceType != I_SLICE, "residualTransformQuantIntra not intended for I slices\n");
695
696 /* we still respect rdPenalty == 2, we can forbid 32x32 intra TU. rdPenalty = 1 is impossible
697 * since we are not measuring RD cost */
698 if (m_param->rdPenalty == 2 && log2TrSize == 5 && depthRange[0] <= 4)
699 bCheckFull = false;
700
701 if (bCheckFull)
702 {
703 const pixel* fenc = mode.fencYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
704 pixel* pred = mode.predYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
705 int16_t* residual = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
706 uint32_t stride = mode.fencYuv->m_size;
707
708 // init availability pattern
709 uint32_t lumaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[absPartIdx];
710 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
711 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdx, tuDepth, true, &intraNeighbors);
712 initAdiPattern(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdx, intraNeighbors, lumaPredMode);
713
714 // get prediction signal
715 predIntraLumaAng(lumaPredMode, pred, stride, log2TrSize);
716
717 X265_CHECK(!cu.m_transformSkip[TEXT_LUMA][absPartIdx], "unexpected tskip flag in residualTransformQuantIntra\n");
718 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(tuDepth, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
719
720 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2);
721 coeff_t* coeffY = cu.m_trCoeff[0] + coeffOffsetY;
722
723 uint32_t sizeIdx = log2TrSize - 2;
724 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].calcresidual[stride % 64 == 0](fenc, pred, residual, stride);
725
726 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
727 pixel* picReconY = reconPic->getLumaAddr(cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdx);
728 intptr_t picStride = reconPic->m_stride;
729
730 uint32_t numSig = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, stride, residual, stride, coeffY, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, false);
731 if (numSig)
732 {
733 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, residual, stride, coeffY, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, true, false, numSig);
734 bool picReconYAlign = (reconPic->m_cuOffsetY[cu.m_cuAddr] + reconPic->m_buOffsetY[cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdx]) % 64 == 0;
735 bool predAlign = mode.predYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, mode.predYuv.m_size) % 64 == 0;
736 bool residualAlign = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getAddrOffset(absPartIdx, m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.m_size)% 64 == 0;
737 bool bufferAlignCheck = (picStride % 64 == 0) && (stride % 64 == 0) && picReconYAlign && predAlign && residualAlign;
738 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].add_ps[bufferAlignCheck](picReconY, picStride, pred, residual, stride, stride);
739 cu.setCbfSubParts(1 << tuDepth, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
740 }
741 else
742 {
743 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(picReconY, picStride, pred, stride);
744 cu.setCbfSubParts(0, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, fullDepth);
745 }
746 }
747 else
748 {
749 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize > depthRange[0], "intra luma split state failure\n");
750
751 /* code split block */
752 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
753 uint32_t cbf = 0;
754 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = absPartIdx; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
755 {
756 residualTransformQuantIntra(mode, cuGeom, qPartIdx, tuDepth + 1, depthRange);
757 cbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth + 1);
758 }
759 cu.m_cbf[0][absPartIdx] |= (cbf << tuDepth);
760 }
761}
762
763void Search::extractIntraResultQT(CUData& cu, Yuv& reconYuv, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx)
764{
765 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
766
767 if (tuDepth == cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx])
768 {
769 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
770
771 // copy transform coefficients
772 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2);
773 coeff_t* coeffSrcY = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[0] + coeffOffsetY;
774 coeff_t* coeffDestY = cu.m_trCoeff[0] + coeffOffsetY;
775 memcpy(coeffDestY, coeffSrcY, sizeof(coeff_t) << (log2TrSize * 2));
776
777 // copy reconstruction
778 m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.copyPartToPartLuma(reconYuv, absPartIdx, log2TrSize);
779 }
780 else
781 {
782 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
783 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
784 extractIntraResultQT(cu, reconYuv, tuDepth + 1, absPartIdx);
785 }
786}
787
788inline void offsetCBFs(uint8_t subTUCBF[2])
789{
790 uint8_t combinedCBF = subTUCBF[0] | subTUCBF[1];
791 subTUCBF[0] = subTUCBF[0] << 1 | combinedCBF;
792 subTUCBF[1] = subTUCBF[1] << 1 | combinedCBF;
793}
794
795/* 4:2:2 post-TU split processing */
796void Search::offsetSubTUCBFs(CUData& cu, TextType ttype, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx)
797{
798 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
799
800 if (log2TrSize == 2)
801 {
802 X265_CHECK(m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
803 ++log2TrSize;
804 }
805
806 uint32_t tuNumParts = 1 << ((log2TrSize - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2 - 1);
807
808 // move the CBFs down a level and set the parent CBF
809 uint8_t subTUCBF[2];
810 subTUCBF[0] = cu.getCbf(absPartIdx , ttype, tuDepth);
811 subTUCBF[1] = cu.getCbf(absPartIdx+ tuNumParts, ttype, tuDepth);
812 offsetCBFs(subTUCBF);
813
814 cu.setCbfPartRange(subTUCBF[0] << tuDepth, ttype, absPartIdx , tuNumParts);
815 cu.setCbfPartRange(subTUCBF[1] << tuDepth, ttype, absPartIdx + tuNumParts, tuNumParts);
816}
817
818/* returns distortion */
819void Search::codeIntraChromaQt(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t absPartIdx, Cost& outCost)
820{
821 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
822 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
823 bool bEnableRDOQ = !!m_param->rdoqLevel;
824
825 if (tuDepth < cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx])
826 {
827 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
828 uint32_t splitCbfU = 0, splitCbfV = 0;
829 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = absPartIdx; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
830 {
831 codeIntraChromaQt(mode, cuGeom, tuDepth + 1, qPartIdx, outCost);
832 splitCbfU |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth + 1);
833 splitCbfV |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth + 1);
834 }
835 cu.m_cbf[1][absPartIdx] |= (splitCbfU << tuDepth);
836 cu.m_cbf[2][absPartIdx] |= (splitCbfV << tuDepth);
837
838 return;
839 }
840
841 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
842 uint32_t tuDepthC = tuDepth;
843 if (log2TrSizeC < 2)
844 {
845 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize == 2 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
846 if (absPartIdx & 3)
847 return;
848 log2TrSizeC = 2;
849 tuDepthC--;
850 }
851
852 if (bEnableRDOQ)
853 m_entropyCoder.estBit(m_entropyCoder.m_estBitsSbac, log2TrSizeC, false);
854
855 bool checkTransformSkip = m_slice->m_pps->bTransformSkipEnabled && log2TrSizeC <= MAX_LOG2_TS_SIZE && !cu.m_tqBypass[0];
856 checkTransformSkip &= !m_param->bEnableTSkipFast || (log2TrSize <= MAX_LOG2_TS_SIZE && cu.m_transformSkip[TEXT_LUMA][absPartIdx]);
857 if (checkTransformSkip)
858 {
859 codeIntraChromaTSkip(mode, cuGeom, tuDepth, tuDepthC, absPartIdx, outCost);
860 return;
861 }
862
863 ShortYuv& resiYuv = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv;
864 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
865 uint32_t stride = mode.fencYuv->m_csize;
866 const uint32_t sizeIdxC = log2TrSizeC - 2;
867
868 uint32_t curPartNum = cuGeom.numPartitions >> tuDepthC * 2;
869 const SplitType splitType = (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422) ? VERTICAL_SPLIT : DONT_SPLIT;
870
871 TURecurse tuIterator(splitType, curPartNum, absPartIdx);
872 do
873 {
874 uint32_t absPartIdxC = tuIterator.absPartIdxTURelCU;
875
876 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
877 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdxC, tuDepthC, false, &intraNeighbors);
878
879 for (uint32_t chromaId = TEXT_CHROMA_U; chromaId <= TEXT_CHROMA_V; chromaId++)
880 {
881 TextType ttype = (TextType)chromaId;
882
883 const pixel* fenc = mode.fencYuv->getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
884 pixel* pred = mode.predYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
885 int16_t* residual = resiYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
886 uint32_t coeffOffsetC = absPartIdxC << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2 - (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift));
887 coeff_t* coeffC = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[chromaId] + coeffOffsetC;
888 pixel* reconQt = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
889 uint32_t reconQtStride = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.m_csize;
890 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
891 pixel* picReconC = reconPic->getChromaAddr(chromaId, cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdxC);
892 intptr_t picStride = reconPic->m_strideC;
893
894 uint32_t chromaPredMode = cu.m_chromaIntraDir[absPartIdxC];
895 if (chromaPredMode == DM_CHROMA_IDX)
896 chromaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[(m_csp == X265_CSP_I444) ? absPartIdxC : 0];
897 if (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422)
898 chromaPredMode = g_chroma422IntraAngleMappingTable[chromaPredMode];
899
900 // init availability pattern
901 initAdiPatternChroma(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdxC, intraNeighbors, chromaId);
902
903 // get prediction signal
904 predIntraChromaAng(chromaPredMode, pred, stride, log2TrSizeC);
905 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(0, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
906
907 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].calcresidual[stride % 64 == 0](fenc, pred, residual, stride);
908
909 uint32_t numSig = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, stride, residual, stride, coeffC, log2TrSizeC, ttype, absPartIdxC, false);
910 if (numSig)
911 {
912 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, residual, stride, coeffC, log2TrSizeC, ttype, true, false, numSig);
913 bool reconQtAlign = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC) % 64 == 0;
914 bool predAlign = mode.predYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC) % 64 == 0;
915 bool residualAlign = resiYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC) % 64 == 0;
916 bool bufferAlignCheck = reconQtAlign && predAlign && residualAlign && (reconQtStride % 64 == 0) && (stride % 64 == 0);
917 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].add_ps[bufferAlignCheck](reconQt, reconQtStride, pred, residual, stride, stride);
918 cu.setCbfPartRange(1 << tuDepth, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
919 }
920 else
921 {
922 // no coded residual, recon = pred
923 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].copy_pp(reconQt, reconQtStride, pred, stride);
924 cu.setCbfPartRange(0, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
925 }
926
927 outCost.distortion += m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(chromaId, primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].sse_pp(reconQt, reconQtStride, fenc, stride));
928
929 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
930 outCost.energy += m_rdCost.psyCost(sizeIdxC, fenc, stride, reconQt, reconQtStride);
931 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
932 outCost.energy += m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fenc, stride, reconQt, reconQtStride, log2TrSizeC, ttype, absPartIdxC);
933
934 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].copy_pp(picReconC, picStride, reconQt, reconQtStride);
935 }
936 }
937 while (tuIterator.isNextSection());
938
939 if (splitType == VERTICAL_SPLIT)
940 {
941 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
942 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
943 }
944}
945
946/* returns distortion */
947void Search::codeIntraChromaTSkip(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t tuDepth, uint32_t tuDepthC, uint32_t absPartIdx, Cost& outCost)
948{
949 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
950 uint32_t fullDepth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
951 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
952 const uint32_t log2TrSizeC = 2;
953 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
954
955 /* At the TU layers above this one, no RDO is performed, only distortion is being measured,
956 * so the entropy coder is not very accurate. The best we can do is return it in the same
957 * condition as it arrived, and to do all bit estimates from the same state. */
958 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot);
959
960 uint32_t curPartNum = cuGeom.numPartitions >> tuDepthC * 2;
961 const SplitType splitType = (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422) ? VERTICAL_SPLIT : DONT_SPLIT;
962
963 TURecurse tuIterator(splitType, curPartNum, absPartIdx);
964 do
965 {
966 uint32_t absPartIdxC = tuIterator.absPartIdxTURelCU;
967
968 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
969 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdxC, tuDepthC, false, &intraNeighbors);
970
971 for (uint32_t chromaId = TEXT_CHROMA_U; chromaId <= TEXT_CHROMA_V; chromaId++)
972 {
973 TextType ttype = (TextType)chromaId;
974
975 const pixel* fenc = mode.fencYuv->getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
976 pixel* pred = mode.predYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
977 int16_t* residual = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
978 uint32_t stride = mode.fencYuv->m_csize;
979 const uint32_t sizeIdxC = log2TrSizeC - 2;
980
981 uint32_t coeffOffsetC = absPartIdxC << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2 - (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift));
982 coeff_t* coeffC = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[chromaId] + coeffOffsetC;
983 pixel* reconQt = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
984 uint32_t reconQtStride = m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.m_csize;
985
986 // init availability pattern
987 initAdiPatternChroma(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdxC, intraNeighbors, chromaId);
988
989 uint32_t chromaPredMode = cu.m_chromaIntraDir[absPartIdxC];
990 if (chromaPredMode == DM_CHROMA_IDX)
991 chromaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[(m_csp == X265_CSP_I444) ? absPartIdxC : 0];
992 if (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422)
993 chromaPredMode = g_chroma422IntraAngleMappingTable[chromaPredMode];
994
995 // get prediction signal
996 predIntraChromaAng(chromaPredMode, pred, stride, log2TrSizeC);
997
998 uint64_t bCost = MAX_INT64;
999 sse_t bDist = 0;
1000 uint32_t bCbf = 0;
1001 uint32_t bEnergy = 0;
1002 int bTSkip = 0;
1003
1004 int checkTransformSkip = 1;
1005 for (int useTSkip = 0; useTSkip <= checkTransformSkip; useTSkip++)
1006 {
1007 coeff_t* coeff = (useTSkip ? m_tsCoeff : coeffC);
1008 pixel* recon = (useTSkip ? m_tsRecon : reconQt);
1009 uint32_t reconStride = (useTSkip ? MAX_TS_SIZE : reconQtStride);
1010
1011 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].calcresidual[stride % 64 == 0](fenc, pred, residual, stride);
1012
1013 uint32_t numSig = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, stride, residual, stride, coeff, log2TrSizeC, ttype, absPartIdxC, useTSkip);
1014 if (numSig)
1015 {
1016 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, residual, stride, coeff, log2TrSizeC, ttype, true, useTSkip, numSig);
1017 bool reconAlign = (useTSkip ? 1 : m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC)) % 64 == 0;
1018 bool predYuvAlign = mode.predYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC) % 64 == 0;
1019 bool residualAlign = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC) % 64 == 0;
1020 bool bufferAlignCheck = reconAlign && predYuvAlign && residualAlign && (reconStride % 64 == 0) && (stride % 64 == 0);
1021 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].add_ps[bufferAlignCheck](recon, reconStride, pred, residual, stride, stride);
1022 cu.setCbfPartRange(1 << tuDepth, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1023 }
1024 else if (useTSkip)
1025 {
1026 checkTransformSkip = 0;
1027 break;
1028 }
1029 else
1030 {
1031 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].copy_pp(recon, reconStride, pred, stride);
1032 cu.setCbfPartRange(0, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1033 }
1034 sse_t tmpDist = primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].sse_pp(recon, reconStride, fenc, stride);
1035 tmpDist = m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(chromaId, tmpDist);
1036
1037 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(useTSkip, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1038
1039 uint32_t tmpBits = 0, tmpEnergy = 0;
1040 if (numSig)
1041 {
1042 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot);
1043 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
1044 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeffNxN(cu, coeff, absPartIdxC, log2TrSizeC, (TextType)chromaId);
1045 tmpBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
1046 }
1047
1048 uint64_t tmpCost;
1049 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
1050 {
1051 tmpEnergy = m_rdCost.psyCost(sizeIdxC, fenc, stride, reconQt, reconQtStride);
1052 tmpCost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(tmpDist, tmpBits, tmpEnergy);
1053 }
1054 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
1055 {
1056 tmpEnergy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fenc, stride, reconQt, reconQtStride, log2TrSizeC, ttype, absPartIdxC);
1057 tmpCost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(tmpDist, tmpBits, tmpEnergy);
1058 }
1059 else
1060 tmpCost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(tmpDist, tmpBits);
1061
1062 if (tmpCost < bCost)
1063 {
1064 bCost = tmpCost;
1065 bDist = tmpDist;
1066 bTSkip = useTSkip;
1067 bCbf = !!numSig;
1068 bEnergy = tmpEnergy;
1069 }
1070 }
1071
1072 if (bTSkip)
1073 {
1074 memcpy(coeffC, m_tsCoeff, sizeof(coeff_t) << (log2TrSizeC * 2));
1075 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].copy_pp(reconQt, reconQtStride, m_tsRecon, MAX_TS_SIZE);
1076 }
1077
1078 cu.setCbfPartRange(bCbf << tuDepth, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1079 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(bTSkip, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1080
1081 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
1082 pixel* reconPicC = reconPic->getChromaAddr(chromaId, cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdxC);
1083 intptr_t picStride = reconPic->m_strideC;
1084 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].copy_pp(reconPicC, picStride, reconQt, reconQtStride);
1085
1086 outCost.distortion += bDist;
1087 outCost.energy += bEnergy;
1088 }
1089 }
1090 while (tuIterator.isNextSection());
1091
1092 if (splitType == VERTICAL_SPLIT)
1093 {
1094 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
1095 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
1096 }
1097
1098 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[fullDepth].rqtRoot);
1099}
1100
1101void Search::extractIntraResultChromaQT(CUData& cu, Yuv& reconYuv, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth)
1102{
1103 uint32_t tuDepthL = cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx];
1104 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
1105 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
1106
1107 if (tuDepthL == tuDepth || log2TrSizeC == 2)
1108 {
1109 // copy transform coefficients
1110 uint32_t numCoeffC = 1 << (log2TrSizeC * 2 + (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422));
1111 uint32_t coeffOffsetC = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2 - (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift));
1112
1113 uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2 - (tuDepthL - tuDepth);
1114 coeff_t* coeffSrcU = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[1] + coeffOffsetC;
1115 coeff_t* coeffSrcV = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[2] + coeffOffsetC;
1116 coeff_t* coeffDstU = cu.m_trCoeff[1] + coeffOffsetC;
1117 coeff_t* coeffDstV = cu.m_trCoeff[2] + coeffOffsetC;
1118 memcpy(coeffDstU, coeffSrcU, sizeof(coeff_t) * numCoeffC);
1119 memcpy(coeffDstV, coeffSrcV, sizeof(coeff_t) * numCoeffC);
1120
1121 // copy reconstruction
1122 m_rqt[qtLayer].reconQtYuv.copyPartToPartChroma(reconYuv, absPartIdx, log2TrSizeC + m_hChromaShift);
1123 }
1124 else
1125 {
1126 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
1127 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
1128 extractIntraResultChromaQT(cu, reconYuv, absPartIdx, tuDepth + 1);
1129 }
1130}
1131
1132void Search::residualQTIntraChroma(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth)
1133{
1134 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
1135 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[absPartIdx] - tuDepth;
1136
1137 if (tuDepth < cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx])
1138 {
1139 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
1140 uint32_t splitCbfU = 0, splitCbfV = 0;
1141 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = absPartIdx; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
1142 {
1143 residualQTIntraChroma(mode, cuGeom, qPartIdx, tuDepth + 1);
1144 splitCbfU |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth + 1);
1145 splitCbfV |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth + 1);
1146 }
1147 cu.m_cbf[1][absPartIdx] |= (splitCbfU << tuDepth);
1148 cu.m_cbf[2][absPartIdx] |= (splitCbfV << tuDepth);
1149
1150 return;
1151 }
1152
1153 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
1154 uint32_t tuDepthC = tuDepth;
1155 if (log2TrSizeC < 2)
1156 {
1157 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize == 2 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
1158 if (absPartIdx & 3)
1159 return;
1160 log2TrSizeC = 2;
1161 tuDepthC--;
1162 }
1163
1164 ShortYuv& resiYuv = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv;
1165 uint32_t stride = mode.fencYuv->m_csize;
1166 const uint32_t sizeIdxC = log2TrSizeC - 2;
1167
1168 uint32_t curPartNum = cuGeom.numPartitions >> tuDepthC * 2;
1169 const SplitType splitType = (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422) ? VERTICAL_SPLIT : DONT_SPLIT;
1170
1171 TURecurse tuIterator(splitType, curPartNum, absPartIdx);
1172 do
1173 {
1174 uint32_t absPartIdxC = tuIterator.absPartIdxTURelCU;
1175
1176 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
1177 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdxC, tuDepthC, false, &intraNeighbors);
1178
1179 for (uint32_t chromaId = TEXT_CHROMA_U; chromaId <= TEXT_CHROMA_V; chromaId++)
1180 {
1181 TextType ttype = (TextType)chromaId;
1182
1183 const pixel* fenc = mode.fencYuv->getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
1184 pixel* pred = mode.predYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
1185 int16_t* residual = resiYuv.getChromaAddr(chromaId, absPartIdxC);
1186 uint32_t coeffOffsetC = absPartIdxC << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2 - (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift));
1187 coeff_t* coeffC = cu.m_trCoeff[ttype] + coeffOffsetC;
1188 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
1189 pixel* picReconC = reconPic->getChromaAddr(chromaId, cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdxC);
1190 intptr_t picStride = reconPic->m_strideC;
1191
1192 uint32_t chromaPredMode = cu.m_chromaIntraDir[absPartIdxC];
1193 if (chromaPredMode == DM_CHROMA_IDX)
1194 chromaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[(m_csp == X265_CSP_I444) ? absPartIdxC : 0];
1195 if (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422)
1196 chromaPredMode = g_chroma422IntraAngleMappingTable[chromaPredMode];
1197
1198 // init availability pattern
1199 initAdiPatternChroma(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdxC, intraNeighbors, chromaId);
1200
1201 // get prediction signal
1202 predIntraChromaAng(chromaPredMode, pred, stride, log2TrSizeC);
1203
1204 X265_CHECK(!cu.m_transformSkip[ttype][0], "transform skip not supported at low RD levels\n");
1205
1206 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].calcresidual[stride % 64 == 0](fenc, pred, residual, stride);
1207
1208 uint32_t numSig = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, stride, residual, stride, coeffC, log2TrSizeC, ttype, absPartIdxC, false);
1209 if (numSig)
1210 {
1211 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, residual, stride, coeffC, log2TrSizeC, ttype, true, false, numSig);
1212 bool picReconCAlign = (reconPic->m_cuOffsetC[cu.m_cuAddr] + reconPic->m_buOffsetC[cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdxC]) % 64 == 0;
1213 bool predAlign = mode.predYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC) % 64 == 0;
1214 bool residualAlign = resiYuv.getChromaAddrOffset(absPartIdxC)% 64 == 0;
1215 bool bufferAlignCheck = picReconCAlign && predAlign && residualAlign && (picStride % 64 == 0) && (stride % 64 == 0);
1216 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].add_ps[bufferAlignCheck](picReconC, picStride, pred, residual, stride, stride);
1217 cu.setCbfPartRange(1 << tuDepth, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1218 }
1219 else
1220 {
1221 // no coded residual, recon = pred
1222 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].copy_pp(picReconC, picStride, pred, stride);
1223 cu.setCbfPartRange(0, ttype, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
1224 }
1225 }
1226 }
1227 while (tuIterator.isNextSection());
1228
1229 if (splitType == VERTICAL_SPLIT)
1230 {
1231 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
1232 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
1233 }
1234}
1235
1236void Search::checkIntra(Mode& intraMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, PartSize partSize)
1237{
1238 CUData& cu = intraMode.cu;
1239
1240 cu.setPartSizeSubParts(partSize);
1241 cu.setPredModeSubParts(MODE_INTRA);
1242
1243 uint32_t tuDepthRange[2];
1244 cu.getIntraTUQtDepthRange(tuDepthRange, 0);
1245
1246 intraMode.initCosts();
1247 intraMode.lumaDistortion += estIntraPredQT(intraMode, cuGeom, tuDepthRange);
1248 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400)
1249 {
1250 intraMode.chromaDistortion += estIntraPredChromaQT(intraMode, cuGeom);
1251 intraMode.distortion += intraMode.lumaDistortion + intraMode.chromaDistortion;
1252 }
1253 else
1254 intraMode.distortion += intraMode.lumaDistortion;
1255 cu.m_distortion[0] = intraMode.distortion;
1256 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
1257 if (m_slice->m_pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled)
1258 m_entropyCoder.codeCUTransquantBypassFlag(cu.m_tqBypass[0]);
1259
1260 int skipFlagBits = 0;
1261 if (!m_slice->isIntra())
1262 {
1263 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
1264 skipFlagBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
1265 m_entropyCoder.codePredMode(cu.m_predMode[0]);
1266 }
1267
1268 m_entropyCoder.codePartSize(cu, 0, cuGeom.depth);
1269 m_entropyCoder.codePredInfo(cu, 0);
1270 intraMode.mvBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits() - skipFlagBits;
1271
1272 bool bCodeDQP = m_slice->m_pps->bUseDQP;
1273 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeff(cu, 0, bCodeDQP, tuDepthRange);
1274 m_entropyCoder.store(intraMode.contexts);
1275 intraMode.totalBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
1276 intraMode.coeffBits = intraMode.totalBits - intraMode.mvBits - skipFlagBits;
1277 const Yuv* fencYuv = intraMode.fencYuv;
1278 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
1279 intraMode.psyEnergy = m_rdCost.psyCost(cuGeom.log2CUSize - 2, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, intraMode.reconYuv.m_buf[0], intraMode.reconYuv.m_size);
1280 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
1281 intraMode.ssimEnergy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, intraMode.reconYuv.m_buf[0], intraMode.reconYuv.m_size, cuGeom.log2CUSize, TEXT_LUMA, 0);
1282
1283 intraMode.resEnergy = primitives.cu[cuGeom.log2CUSize - 2].sse_pp(intraMode.fencYuv->m_buf[0], intraMode.fencYuv->m_size, intraMode.predYuv.m_buf[0], intraMode.predYuv.m_size);
1284
1285 updateModeCost(intraMode);
1286 checkDQP(intraMode, cuGeom);
1287}
1288
1289/* Note that this function does not save the best intra prediction, it must
1290 * be generated later. It records the best mode in the cu */
1291void Search::checkIntraInInter(Mode& intraMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
1292{
1293 ProfileCUScope(intraMode.cu, intraAnalysisElapsedTime, countIntraAnalysis);
1294
1295 CUData& cu = intraMode.cu;
1296 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth;
1297
1298 cu.setPartSizeSubParts(SIZE_2Nx2N);
1299 cu.setPredModeSubParts(MODE_INTRA);
1300
1301 const uint32_t initTuDepth = 0;
1302 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - initTuDepth;
1303 uint32_t tuSize = 1 << log2TrSize;
1304 const uint32_t absPartIdx = 0;
1305
1306 // Reference sample smoothing
1307 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
1308 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdx, initTuDepth, true, &intraNeighbors);
1309 initAdiPattern(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdx, intraNeighbors, ALL_IDX);
1310
1311 const pixel* fenc = intraMode.fencYuv->m_buf[0];
1312 uint32_t stride = intraMode.fencYuv->m_size;
1313
1314 int sad, bsad;
1315 uint32_t bits, bbits, mode, bmode;
1316 uint64_t cost, bcost;
1317
1318 // 33 Angle modes once
1319 int scaleTuSize = tuSize;
1320 int scaleStride = stride;
1321 int costShift = 0;
1322 int sizeIdx = log2TrSize - 2;
1323
1324 if (tuSize > 32)
1325 {
1326 // CU is 64x64, we scale to 32x32 and adjust required parameters
1327 primitives.scale2D_64to32(m_fencScaled, fenc, stride);
1328 fenc = m_fencScaled;
1329
1330 pixel nScale[129];
1331 intraNeighbourBuf[1][0] = intraNeighbourBuf[0][0];
1332 primitives.scale1D_128to64[NONALIGNED](nScale + 1, intraNeighbourBuf[0] + 1);
1333
1334 // we do not estimate filtering for downscaled samples
1335 memcpy(&intraNeighbourBuf[0][1], &nScale[1], 2 * 64 * sizeof(pixel)); // Top & Left pixels
1336 memcpy(&intraNeighbourBuf[1][1], &nScale[1], 2 * 64 * sizeof(pixel));
1337
1338 scaleTuSize = 32;
1339 scaleStride = 32;
1340 costShift = 2;
1341 sizeIdx = 5 - 2; // log2(scaleTuSize) - 2
1342 }
1343
1344 pixelcmp_t sa8d = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sa8d;
1345 int predsize = scaleTuSize * scaleTuSize;
1346
1347 m_entropyCoder.loadIntraDirModeLuma(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1348
1349 /* there are three cost tiers for intra modes:
1350 * pred[0] - mode probable, least cost
1351 * pred[1], pred[2] - less probable, slightly more cost
1352 * non-mpm modes - all cost the same (rbits) */
1353 uint64_t mpms;
1354 uint32_t mpmModes[3];
1355 uint32_t rbits = getIntraRemModeBits(cu, absPartIdx, mpmModes, mpms);
1356
1357 // DC
1358 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[DC_IDX](m_intraPredAngs, scaleStride, intraNeighbourBuf[0], 0, (scaleTuSize <= 16));
1359 bsad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, m_intraPredAngs, scaleStride) << costShift;
1360 bmode = mode = DC_IDX;
1361 bbits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << mode)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, mode) : rbits;
1362 bcost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(bsad, bbits);
1363
1364 // PLANAR
1365 pixel* planar = intraNeighbourBuf[0];
1366 if (tuSize & (8 | 16 | 32))
1367 planar = intraNeighbourBuf[1];
1368
1369 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[PLANAR_IDX](m_intraPredAngs, scaleStride, planar, 0, 0);
1370 sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, m_intraPredAngs, scaleStride) << costShift;
1371 mode = PLANAR_IDX;
1372 bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << mode)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, mode) : rbits;
1373 cost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits);
1374 COPY4_IF_LT(bcost, cost, bmode, mode, bsad, sad, bbits, bits);
1375
1376 bool allangs = true;
1377 if (primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred_allangs)
1378 {
1379 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].transpose(m_fencTransposed, fenc, scaleStride);
1380 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred_allangs(m_intraPredAngs, intraNeighbourBuf[0], intraNeighbourBuf[1], (scaleTuSize <= 16));
1381 }
1382 else
1383 allangs = false;
1384
1385#define TRY_ANGLE(angle) \
1386 if (allangs) { \
1387 if (angle < 18) \
1388 sad = sa8d(m_fencTransposed, scaleTuSize, &m_intraPredAngs[(angle - 2) * predsize], scaleTuSize) << costShift; \
1389 else \
1390 sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, &m_intraPredAngs[(angle - 2) * predsize], scaleTuSize) << costShift; \
1391 bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << angle)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, angle) : rbits; \
1392 cost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits); \
1393 } else { \
1394 int filter = !!(g_intraFilterFlags[angle] & scaleTuSize); \
1395 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[angle](m_intraPredAngs, scaleTuSize, intraNeighbourBuf[filter], angle, scaleTuSize <= 16); \
1396 sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, m_intraPredAngs, scaleTuSize) << costShift; \
1397 bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << angle)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, angle) : rbits; \
1398 cost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits); \
1399 }
1400
1401 if (m_param->bEnableFastIntra)
1402 {
1403 int asad = 0;
1404 uint32_t lowmode, highmode, amode = 5, abits = 0;
1405 uint64_t acost = MAX_INT64;
1406
1407 /* pick the best angle, sampling at distance of 5 */
1408 for (mode = 5; mode < 35; mode += 5)
1409 {
1410 TRY_ANGLE(mode);
1411 COPY4_IF_LT(acost, cost, amode, mode, asad, sad, abits, bits);
1412 }
1413
1414 /* refine best angle at distance 2, then distance 1 */
1415 for (uint32_t dist = 2; dist >= 1; dist--)
1416 {
1417 lowmode = amode - dist;
1418 highmode = amode + dist;
1419
1420 X265_CHECK(lowmode >= 2 && lowmode <= 34, "low intra mode out of range\n");
1421 TRY_ANGLE(lowmode);
1422 COPY4_IF_LT(acost, cost, amode, lowmode, asad, sad, abits, bits);
1423
1424 X265_CHECK(highmode >= 2 && highmode <= 34, "high intra mode out of range\n");
1425 TRY_ANGLE(highmode);
1426 COPY4_IF_LT(acost, cost, amode, highmode, asad, sad, abits, bits);
1427 }
1428
1429 if (amode == 33)
1430 {
1431 TRY_ANGLE(34);
1432 COPY4_IF_LT(acost, cost, amode, 34, asad, sad, abits, bits);
1433 }
1434
1435 COPY4_IF_LT(bcost, acost, bmode, amode, bsad, asad, bbits, abits);
1436 }
1437 else // calculate and search all intra prediction angles for lowest cost
1438 {
1439 for (mode = 2; mode < 35; mode++)
1440 {
1441 TRY_ANGLE(mode);
1442 COPY4_IF_LT(bcost, cost, bmode, mode, bsad, sad, bbits, bits);
1443 }
1444 }
1445
1446 cu.setLumaIntraDirSubParts((uint8_t)bmode, absPartIdx, depth + initTuDepth);
1447 intraMode.initCosts();
1448 intraMode.totalBits = bbits;
1449 intraMode.distortion = bsad;
1450 intraMode.sa8dCost = bcost;
1451 intraMode.sa8dBits = bbits;
1452}
1453
1454void Search::encodeIntraInInter(Mode& intraMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
1455{
1456 ProfileCUScope(intraMode.cu, intraRDOElapsedTime[cuGeom.depth], countIntraRDO[cuGeom.depth]);
1457
1458 CUData& cu = intraMode.cu;
1459 Yuv* reconYuv = &intraMode.reconYuv;
1460
1461 X265_CHECK(cu.m_partSize[0] == SIZE_2Nx2N, "encodeIntraInInter does not expect NxN intra\n");
1462 X265_CHECK(!m_slice->isIntra(), "encodeIntraInInter does not expect to be used in I slices\n");
1463
1464 uint32_t tuDepthRange[2];
1465 cu.getIntraTUQtDepthRange(tuDepthRange, 0);
1466
1467 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].cur);
1468
1469 Cost icosts;
1470 codeIntraLumaQT(intraMode, cuGeom, 0, 0, false, icosts, tuDepthRange);
1471 extractIntraResultQT(cu, *reconYuv, 0, 0);
1472
1473 intraMode.lumaDistortion = icosts.distortion;
1474 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400)
1475 {
1476 intraMode.chromaDistortion = estIntraPredChromaQT(intraMode, cuGeom);
1477 intraMode.distortion = intraMode.lumaDistortion + intraMode.chromaDistortion;
1478 }
1479 else
1480 intraMode.distortion = intraMode.lumaDistortion;
1481
1482 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
1483 if (m_slice->m_pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled)
1484 m_entropyCoder.codeCUTransquantBypassFlag(cu.m_tqBypass[0]);
1485 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
1486 int skipFlagBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
1487 m_entropyCoder.codePredMode(cu.m_predMode[0]);
1488 m_entropyCoder.codePartSize(cu, 0, cuGeom.depth);
1489 m_entropyCoder.codePredInfo(cu, 0);
1490 intraMode.mvBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits() - skipFlagBits;
1491
1492 bool bCodeDQP = m_slice->m_pps->bUseDQP;
1493 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeff(cu, 0, bCodeDQP, tuDepthRange);
1494
1495 intraMode.totalBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
1496 intraMode.coeffBits = intraMode.totalBits - intraMode.mvBits - skipFlagBits;
1497 const Yuv* fencYuv = intraMode.fencYuv;
1498 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
1499 intraMode.psyEnergy = m_rdCost.psyCost(cuGeom.log2CUSize - 2, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size);
1500 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
1501 intraMode.ssimEnergy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size, cuGeom.log2CUSize, TEXT_LUMA, 0);
1502
1503 intraMode.resEnergy = primitives.cu[cuGeom.log2CUSize - 2].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, intraMode.predYuv.m_buf[0], intraMode.predYuv.m_size);
1504 m_entropyCoder.store(intraMode.contexts);
1505 updateModeCost(intraMode);
1506 checkDQP(intraMode, cuGeom);
1507}
1508
1509sse_t Search::estIntraPredQT(Mode &intraMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, const uint32_t depthRange[2])
1510{
1511 CUData& cu = intraMode.cu;
1512 Yuv* reconYuv = &intraMode.reconYuv;
1513 Yuv* predYuv = &intraMode.predYuv;
1514 const Yuv* fencYuv = intraMode.fencYuv;
1515
1516 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth;
1517 uint32_t initTuDepth = cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N;
1518 uint32_t numPU = 1 << (2 * initTuDepth);
1519 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - initTuDepth;
1520 uint32_t tuSize = 1 << log2TrSize;
1521 uint32_t qNumParts = cuGeom.numPartitions >> 2;
1522 uint32_t sizeIdx = log2TrSize - 2;
1523 uint32_t absPartIdx = 0;
1524 sse_t totalDistortion = 0;
1525
1526 int checkTransformSkip = m_slice->m_pps->bTransformSkipEnabled && !cu.m_tqBypass[0] && cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N;
1527
1528 // loop over partitions
1529 for (uint32_t puIdx = 0; puIdx < numPU; puIdx++, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
1530 {
1531 uint32_t bmode = 0;
1532
1533 if (intraMode.cu.m_lumaIntraDir[puIdx] != (uint8_t)ALL_IDX)
1534 bmode = intraMode.cu.m_lumaIntraDir[puIdx];
1535 else
1536 {
1537 uint64_t candCostList[MAX_RD_INTRA_MODES];
1538 uint32_t rdModeList[MAX_RD_INTRA_MODES];
1539 uint64_t bcost;
1540 int maxCandCount = 2 + m_param->rdLevel + ((depth + initTuDepth) >> 1);
1541
1542 {
1543 ProfileCUScope(intraMode.cu, intraAnalysisElapsedTime, countIntraAnalysis);
1544
1545 // Reference sample smoothing
1546 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
1547 initIntraNeighbors(cu, absPartIdx, initTuDepth, true, &intraNeighbors);
1548 initAdiPattern(cu, cuGeom, absPartIdx, intraNeighbors, ALL_IDX);
1549
1550 // determine set of modes to be tested (using prediction signal only)
1551 const pixel* fenc = fencYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
1552 uint32_t stride = predYuv->m_size;
1553
1554 int scaleTuSize = tuSize;
1555 int scaleStride = stride;
1556 int costShift = 0;
1557
1558 m_entropyCoder.loadIntraDirModeLuma(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1559
1560 /* there are three cost tiers for intra modes:
1561 * pred[0] - mode probable, least cost
1562 * pred[1], pred[2] - less probable, slightly more cost
1563 * non-mpm modes - all cost the same (rbits) */
1564 uint64_t mpms;
1565 uint32_t mpmModes[3];
1566 uint32_t rbits = getIntraRemModeBits(cu, absPartIdx, mpmModes, mpms);
1567
1568 pixelcmp_t sa8d = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sa8d;
1569 uint64_t modeCosts[35];
1570
1571 // DC
1572 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[DC_IDX](m_intraPred, scaleStride, intraNeighbourBuf[0], 0, (scaleTuSize <= 16));
1573 uint32_t bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << DC_IDX)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, DC_IDX) : rbits;
1574 uint32_t sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, m_intraPred, scaleStride) << costShift;
1575 modeCosts[DC_IDX] = bcost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits);
1576
1577 // PLANAR
1578 pixel* planar = intraNeighbourBuf[0];
1579 if (tuSize >= 8 && tuSize <= 32)
1580 planar = intraNeighbourBuf[1];
1581
1582 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[PLANAR_IDX](m_intraPred, scaleStride, planar, 0, 0);
1583 bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << PLANAR_IDX)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, PLANAR_IDX) : rbits;
1584 sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, m_intraPred, scaleStride) << costShift;
1585 modeCosts[PLANAR_IDX] = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits);
1586 COPY1_IF_LT(bcost, modeCosts[PLANAR_IDX]);
1587
1588 // angular predictions
1589 if (primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred_allangs)
1590 {
1591 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].transpose(m_fencTransposed, fenc, scaleStride);
1592 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred_allangs(m_intraPredAngs, intraNeighbourBuf[0], intraNeighbourBuf[1], (scaleTuSize <= 16));
1593 for (int mode = 2; mode < 35; mode++)
1594 {
1595 bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << mode)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, mode) : rbits;
1596 if (mode < 18)
1597 sad = sa8d(m_fencTransposed, scaleTuSize, &m_intraPredAngs[(mode - 2) * (scaleTuSize * scaleTuSize)], scaleTuSize) << costShift;
1598 else
1599 sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, &m_intraPredAngs[(mode - 2) * (scaleTuSize * scaleTuSize)], scaleTuSize) << costShift;
1600 modeCosts[mode] = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits);
1601 COPY1_IF_LT(bcost, modeCosts[mode]);
1602 }
1603 }
1604 else
1605 {
1606 for (int mode = 2; mode < 35; mode++)
1607 {
1608 bits = (mpms & ((uint64_t)1 << mode)) ? m_entropyCoder.bitsIntraModeMPM(mpmModes, mode) : rbits;
1609 int filter = !!(g_intraFilterFlags[mode] & scaleTuSize);
1610 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[mode](m_intraPred, scaleTuSize, intraNeighbourBuf[filter], mode, scaleTuSize <= 16);
1611 sad = sa8d(fenc, scaleStride, m_intraPred, scaleTuSize) << costShift;
1612 modeCosts[mode] = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost(sad, bits);
1613 COPY1_IF_LT(bcost, modeCosts[mode]);
1614 }
1615 }
1616
1617 /* Find the top maxCandCount candidate modes with cost within 25% of best
1618 * or among the most probable modes. maxCandCount is derived from the
1619 * rdLevel and depth. In general we want to try more modes at slower RD
1620 * levels and at higher depths */
1621 for (int i = 0; i < maxCandCount; i++)
1622 candCostList[i] = MAX_INT64;
1623
1624 uint64_t paddedBcost = bcost + (bcost >> 2); // 1.25%
1625 for (int mode = 0; mode < 35; mode++)
1626 if ((modeCosts[mode] < paddedBcost) || ((uint32_t)mode == mpmModes[0]))
1627 /* choose for R-D analysis only if this mode passes cost threshold or matches MPM[0] */
1628 updateCandList(mode, modeCosts[mode], maxCandCount, rdModeList, candCostList);
1629 }
1630
1631 /* measure best candidates using simple RDO (no TU splits) */
1632 bcost = MAX_INT64;
1633 for (int i = 0; i < maxCandCount; i++)
1634 {
1635 if (candCostList[i] == MAX_INT64)
1636 break;
1637
1638 ProfileCUScope(intraMode.cu, intraRDOElapsedTime[cuGeom.depth], countIntraRDO[cuGeom.depth]);
1639
1640 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1641 cu.setLumaIntraDirSubParts(rdModeList[i], absPartIdx, depth + initTuDepth);
1642
1643 Cost icosts;
1644 if (checkTransformSkip)
1645 codeIntraLumaTSkip(intraMode, cuGeom, initTuDepth, absPartIdx, icosts);
1646 else
1647 codeIntraLumaQT(intraMode, cuGeom, initTuDepth, absPartIdx, false, icosts, depthRange);
1648 COPY2_IF_LT(bcost, icosts.rdcost, bmode, rdModeList[i]);
1649 }
1650 }
1651
1652 ProfileCUScope(intraMode.cu, intraRDOElapsedTime[cuGeom.depth], countIntraRDO[cuGeom.depth]);
1653
1654 /* remeasure best mode, allowing TU splits */
1655 cu.setLumaIntraDirSubParts(bmode, absPartIdx, depth + initTuDepth);
1656 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1657
1658 Cost icosts;
1659 if (checkTransformSkip)
1660 codeIntraLumaTSkip(intraMode, cuGeom, initTuDepth, absPartIdx, icosts);
1661 else
1662 codeIntraLumaQT(intraMode, cuGeom, initTuDepth, absPartIdx, true, icosts, depthRange);
1663 totalDistortion += icosts.distortion;
1664
1665 extractIntraResultQT(cu, *reconYuv, initTuDepth, absPartIdx);
1666
1667 // set reconstruction for next intra prediction blocks
1668 if (puIdx != numPU - 1)
1669 {
1670 /* This has important implications for parallelism and RDO. It is writing intermediate results into the
1671 * output recon picture, so it cannot proceed in parallel with anything else when doing INTRA_NXN. Also
1672 * it is not updating m_rdContexts[depth].cur for the later PUs which I suspect is slightly wrong. I think
1673 * that the contexts should be tracked through each PU */
1674 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
1675 pixel* dst = reconPic->getLumaAddr(cu.m_cuAddr, cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdx);
1676 uint32_t dststride = reconPic->m_stride;
1677 const pixel* src = reconYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
1678 uint32_t srcstride = reconYuv->m_size;
1679 primitives.cu[log2TrSize - 2].copy_pp(dst, dststride, src, srcstride);
1680 }
1681 }
1682
1683 if (numPU > 1)
1684 {
1685 uint32_t combCbfY = 0;
1686 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
1687 combCbfY |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, 1);
1688
1689 cu.m_cbf[0][0] |= combCbfY;
1690 }
1691
1692 // TODO: remove this
1693 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1694
1695 return totalDistortion;
1696}
1697
1698void Search::getBestIntraModeChroma(Mode& intraMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
1699{
1700 CUData& cu = intraMode.cu;
1701 const Yuv* fencYuv = intraMode.fencYuv;
1702 Yuv* predYuv = &intraMode.predYuv;
1703
1704 uint32_t bestMode = 0;
1705 uint64_t bestCost = MAX_INT64;
1706 uint32_t modeList[NUM_CHROMA_MODE];
1707
1708 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - m_hChromaShift;
1709 uint32_t tuSize = 1 << log2TrSizeC;
1710 uint32_t tuDepth = 0;
1711 int32_t costShift = 0;
1712
1713 if (tuSize > 32)
1714 {
1715 tuDepth = 1;
1716 costShift = 2;
1717 log2TrSizeC = 5;
1718 }
1719
1720 IntraNeighbors intraNeighbors;
1721 initIntraNeighbors(cu, 0, tuDepth, false, &intraNeighbors);
1722 cu.getAllowedChromaDir(0, modeList);
1723
1724 // check chroma modes
1725 for (uint32_t mode = 0; mode < NUM_CHROMA_MODE; mode++)
1726 {
1727 uint32_t chromaPredMode = modeList[mode];
1728 if (chromaPredMode == DM_CHROMA_IDX)
1729 chromaPredMode = cu.m_lumaIntraDir[0];
1730 if (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422)
1731 chromaPredMode = g_chroma422IntraAngleMappingTable[chromaPredMode];
1732
1733 uint64_t cost = 0;
1734 for (uint32_t chromaId = TEXT_CHROMA_U; chromaId <= TEXT_CHROMA_V; chromaId++)
1735 {
1736 const pixel* fenc = fencYuv->m_buf[chromaId];
1737 pixel* pred = predYuv->m_buf[chromaId];
1738 Predict::initAdiPatternChroma(cu, cuGeom, 0, intraNeighbors, chromaId);
1739 // get prediction signal
1740 predIntraChromaAng(chromaPredMode, pred, fencYuv->m_csize, log2TrSizeC);
1741 cost += primitives.cu[log2TrSizeC - 2].sa8d(fenc, predYuv->m_csize, pred, fencYuv->m_csize) << costShift;
1742 }
1743
1744 if (cost < bestCost)
1745 {
1746 bestCost = cost;
1747 bestMode = modeList[mode];
1748 }
1749 }
1750
1751 cu.setChromIntraDirSubParts(bestMode, 0, cuGeom.depth);
1752}
1753
1754sse_t Search::estIntraPredChromaQT(Mode &intraMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
1755{
1756 CUData& cu = intraMode.cu;
1757 Yuv& reconYuv = intraMode.reconYuv;
1758
1759 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth;
1760 uint32_t initTuDepth = cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N && m_csp == X265_CSP_I444;
1761 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - initTuDepth;
1762 uint32_t absPartStep = cuGeom.numPartitions;
1763 sse_t totalDistortion = 0;
1764
1765 int size = partitionFromLog2Size(log2TrSize);
1766
1767 TURecurse tuIterator((initTuDepth == 0) ? DONT_SPLIT : QUAD_SPLIT, absPartStep, 0);
1768
1769 do
1770 {
1771 uint32_t absPartIdxC = tuIterator.absPartIdxTURelCU;
1772
1773 uint32_t bestMode = 0;
1774 sse_t bestDist = 0;
1775 uint64_t bestCost = MAX_INT64;
1776
1777 // init mode list
1778 uint32_t minMode = 0;
1779 uint32_t maxMode = NUM_CHROMA_MODE;
1780 uint32_t modeList[NUM_CHROMA_MODE];
1781
1782 if (intraMode.cu.m_chromaIntraDir[0] != (uint8_t)ALL_IDX && !initTuDepth)
1783 {
1784 for (uint32_t l = 0; l < NUM_CHROMA_MODE; l++)
1785 modeList[l] = intraMode.cu.m_chromaIntraDir[0];
1786 maxMode = 1;
1787 }
1788 else
1789 cu.getAllowedChromaDir(absPartIdxC, modeList);
1790
1791 if (m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp == X265_CSP_I400 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I400)
1792 {
1793 for (uint32_t l = 1; l < NUM_CHROMA_MODE; l++)
1794 modeList[l] = modeList[0];
1795 maxMode = 1;
1796 }
1797 // check chroma modes
1798 for (uint32_t mode = minMode; mode < maxMode; mode++)
1799 {
1800 // restore context models
1801 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1802
1803 cu.setChromIntraDirSubParts(modeList[mode], absPartIdxC, depth + initTuDepth);
1804 Cost outCost;
1805 codeIntraChromaQt(intraMode, cuGeom, initTuDepth, absPartIdxC, outCost);
1806
1807 if (m_slice->m_pps->bTransformSkipEnabled)
1808 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1809
1810 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
1811 // chroma prediction mode
1812 if (cu.m_partSize[0] == SIZE_2Nx2N || m_csp != X265_CSP_I444)
1813 {
1814 if (!absPartIdxC)
1815 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirChroma(cu, absPartIdxC, modeList);
1816 }
1817 else
1818 {
1819 uint32_t qNumParts = cuGeom.numPartitions >> 2;
1820 if (!(absPartIdxC & (qNumParts - 1)))
1821 m_entropyCoder.codeIntraDirChroma(cu, absPartIdxC, modeList);
1822 }
1823
1824 codeSubdivCbfQTChroma(cu, initTuDepth, absPartIdxC);
1825 codeCoeffQTChroma(cu, initTuDepth, absPartIdxC, TEXT_CHROMA_U);
1826 codeCoeffQTChroma(cu, initTuDepth, absPartIdxC, TEXT_CHROMA_V);
1827 uint32_t bits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
1828 uint64_t cost = m_rdCost.m_psyRd ? m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(outCost.distortion, bits, outCost.energy) : m_rdCost.m_ssimRd ? m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(outCost.distortion, bits, outCost.energy)
1829 : m_rdCost.calcRdCost(outCost.distortion, bits);
1830
1831 if (cost < bestCost)
1832 {
1833 bestCost = cost;
1834 bestDist = outCost.distortion;
1835 bestMode = modeList[mode];
1836 extractIntraResultChromaQT(cu, reconYuv, absPartIdxC, initTuDepth);
1837 memcpy(m_qtTempCbf[1], cu.m_cbf[1] + absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1838 memcpy(m_qtTempCbf[2], cu.m_cbf[2] + absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1839 memcpy(m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[1], cu.m_transformSkip[1] + absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1840 memcpy(m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[2], cu.m_transformSkip[2] + absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1841 }
1842 }
1843
1844 if (!tuIterator.isLastSection())
1845 {
1846 uint32_t zorder = cuGeom.absPartIdx + absPartIdxC;
1847 PicYuv* reconPic = m_frame->m_reconPic;
1848 uint32_t dststride = reconPic->m_strideC;
1849 const pixel* src;
1850 pixel* dst;
1851
1852 dst = reconPic->getCbAddr(cu.m_cuAddr, zorder);
1853 src = reconYuv.getCbAddr(absPartIdxC);
1854 primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[size].copy_pp(dst, dststride, src, reconYuv.m_csize);
1855
1856 dst = reconPic->getCrAddr(cu.m_cuAddr, zorder);
1857 src = reconYuv.getCrAddr(absPartIdxC);
1858 primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[size].copy_pp(dst, dststride, src, reconYuv.m_csize);
1859 }
1860
1861 memcpy(cu.m_cbf[1] + absPartIdxC, m_qtTempCbf[1], tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1862 memcpy(cu.m_cbf[2] + absPartIdxC, m_qtTempCbf[2], tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1863 memcpy(cu.m_transformSkip[1] + absPartIdxC, m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[1], tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1864 memcpy(cu.m_transformSkip[2] + absPartIdxC, m_qtTempTransformSkipFlag[2], tuIterator.absPartIdxStep * sizeof(uint8_t));
1865 cu.setChromIntraDirSubParts(bestMode, absPartIdxC, depth + initTuDepth);
1866 totalDistortion += bestDist;
1867 }
1868 while (tuIterator.isNextSection());
1869
1870 if (initTuDepth != 0)
1871 {
1872 uint32_t combCbfU = 0;
1873 uint32_t combCbfV = 0;
1874 uint32_t qNumParts = tuIterator.absPartIdxStep;
1875 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
1876 {
1877 combCbfU |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, 1);
1878 combCbfV |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, 1);
1879 }
1880
1881 cu.m_cbf[1][0] |= combCbfU;
1882 cu.m_cbf[2][0] |= combCbfV;
1883 }
1884
1885 /* TODO: remove this */
1886 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
1887 return totalDistortion;
1888}
1889
1890/* estimation of best merge coding of an inter PU (2Nx2N merge PUs are evaluated as their own mode) */
1891uint32_t Search::mergeEstimation(CUData& cu, const CUGeom& cuGeom, const PredictionUnit& pu, int puIdx, MergeData& m)
1892{
1893 X265_CHECK(cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N, "mergeEstimation() called for 2Nx2N\n");
1894
1895 MVField candMvField[MRG_MAX_NUM_CANDS][2];
1896 uint8_t candDir[MRG_MAX_NUM_CANDS];
1897 uint32_t numMergeCand = cu.getInterMergeCandidates(pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx, candMvField, candDir);
1898
1899 if (cu.isBipredRestriction())
1900 {
1901 /* do not allow bidir merge candidates if PU is smaller than 8x8, drop L1 reference */
1902 for (uint32_t mergeCand = 0; mergeCand < numMergeCand; ++mergeCand)
1903 {
1904 if (candDir[mergeCand] == 3)
1905 {
1906 candDir[mergeCand] = 1;
1907 candMvField[mergeCand][1].refIdx = REF_NOT_VALID;
1908 }
1909 }
1910 }
1911
1912 Yuv& tempYuv = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpPredYuv;
1913
1914 uint32_t outCost = MAX_UINT;
1915 for (uint32_t mergeCand = 0; mergeCand < numMergeCand; ++mergeCand)
1916 {
1917 /* Prevent TMVP candidates from using unavailable reference pixels */
1918 if (m_bFrameParallel)
1919 {
1920 // Parallel slices bound check
1921 if (m_param->maxSlices > 1)
1922 {
1923 if (cu.m_bFirstRowInSlice &
1924 ((candMvField[mergeCand][0].mv.y < (2 * 4)) | (candMvField[mergeCand][1].mv.y < (2 * 4))))
1925 continue;
1926
1927 // Last row in slice can't reference beyond bound since it is another slice area
1928 // TODO: we may beyond bound in future since these area have a chance to finish because we use parallel slices. Necessary prepare research on load balance
1929 if (cu.m_bLastRowInSlice &&
1930 ((candMvField[mergeCand][0].mv.y > -3 * 4) | (candMvField[mergeCand][1].mv.y > -3 * 4)))
1931 continue;
1932 }
1933
1934 if (candMvField[mergeCand][0].mv.y >= (m_param->searchRange + 1) * 4 ||
1935 candMvField[mergeCand][1].mv.y >= (m_param->searchRange + 1) * 4)
1936 continue;
1937 }
1938
1939 cu.m_mv[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = candMvField[mergeCand][0].mv;
1940 cu.m_refIdx[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = (int8_t)candMvField[mergeCand][0].refIdx;
1941 cu.m_mv[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = candMvField[mergeCand][1].mv;
1942 cu.m_refIdx[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = (int8_t)candMvField[mergeCand][1].refIdx;
1943
1944 motionCompensation(cu, pu, tempYuv, true, m_me.bChromaSATD);
1945
1946 uint32_t costCand = m_me.bufSATD(tempYuv.getLumaAddr(pu.puAbsPartIdx), tempYuv.m_size);
1947 if (m_me.bChromaSATD)
1948 costCand += m_me.bufChromaSATD(tempYuv, pu.puAbsPartIdx);
1949
1950 uint32_t bitsCand = getTUBits(mergeCand, numMergeCand);
1951 costCand = costCand + m_rdCost.getCost(bitsCand);
1952 if (costCand < outCost)
1953 {
1954 outCost = costCand;
1955 m.bits = bitsCand;
1956 m.index = mergeCand;
1957 }
1958 }
1959
1960 m.mvField[0] = candMvField[m.index][0];
1961 m.mvField[1] = candMvField[m.index][1];
1962 m.dir = candDir[m.index];
1963
1964 return outCost;
1965}
1966
1967/* find the lowres motion vector from lookahead in middle of current PU */
1968MV Search::getLowresMV(const CUData& cu, const PredictionUnit& pu, int list, int ref)
1969{
1970 int diffPoc = abs(m_slice->m_poc - m_slice->m_refPOCList[list][ref]);
1971 if (diffPoc > m_param->bframes + 1)
1972 /* poc difference is out of range for lookahead */
1973 return 0;
1974
1975 MV* mvs = m_frame->m_lowres.lowresMvs[list][diffPoc];
1976 if (mvs[0].x == 0x7FFF)
1977 /* this motion search was not estimated by lookahead */
1978 return 0;
1979
1980 uint32_t block_x = (cu.m_cuPelX + g_zscanToPelX[pu.puAbsPartIdx] + pu.width / 2) >> 4;
1981 uint32_t block_y = (cu.m_cuPelY + g_zscanToPelY[pu.puAbsPartIdx] + pu.height / 2) >> 4;
1982 uint32_t idx = block_y * m_frame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRow + block_x;
1983
1984 X265_CHECK(block_x < m_frame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRow, "block_x is too high\n");
1985 X265_CHECK(block_y < m_frame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInCol, "block_y is too high\n");
1986
1987 return mvs[idx] << 1; /* scale up lowres mv */
1988}
1989
1990/* Pick between the two AMVP candidates which is the best one to use as
1991 * MVP for the motion search, based on SAD cost */
1992int Search::selectMVP(const CUData& cu, const PredictionUnit& pu, const MV amvp[AMVP_NUM_CANDS], int list, int ref)
1993{
1994 if (amvp[0] == amvp[1])
1995 return 0;
1996
1997 Yuv& tmpPredYuv = m_rqt[cu.m_cuDepth[0]].tmpPredYuv;
1998 uint32_t costs[AMVP_NUM_CANDS];
1999
2000 for (int i = 0; i < AMVP_NUM_CANDS; i++)
2001 {
2002 MV mvCand = amvp[i];
2003
2004 // NOTE: skip mvCand if Y is > merange and -FN>1
2005 if (m_bFrameParallel)
2006 {
2007 costs[i] = m_me.COST_MAX;
2008
2009 if (mvCand.y >= (m_param->searchRange + 1) * 4)
2010 continue;
2011
2012 if ((m_param->maxSlices > 1) &
2013 ((mvCand.y < m_sliceMinY)
2014 | (mvCand.y > m_sliceMaxY)))
2015 continue;
2016 }
2017 cu.clipMv(mvCand);
2018 predInterLumaPixel(pu, tmpPredYuv, *m_slice->m_refReconPicList[list][ref], mvCand);
2019 costs[i] = m_me.bufSAD(tmpPredYuv.getLumaAddr(pu.puAbsPartIdx), tmpPredYuv.m_size);
2020 }
2021
2022 return (costs[0] <= costs[1]) ? 0 : 1;
2023}

2028 int fe = mode.cu.m_encData->m_frameEncoderID;
2029 master.m_stats[fe].countPMETasks++;
2030 ScopedElapsedTime pmeTime(master.m_stats[fe].pmeTime);
