2035
2036void Search::processPME(PME& pme, Search& slave)
2037{
2038 /* acquire a motion estimation job, else exit early */
2039 int meId;
2040 pme.m_lock.acquire();
2041 if (pme.m_jobTotal > pme.m_jobAcquired)
2042 {
2043 meId = pme.m_jobAcquired++;
2044 pme.m_lock.release();
2045 }
2046 else
2047 {
2048 pme.m_lock.release();
2049 return;
2050 }
2051
2052 /* Setup slave Search instance for ME for master's CU */
2053 if (&slave != this)
2054 {
2055 slave.m_slice = m_slice;
2056 slave.m_frame = m_frame;
2057 slave.m_param = m_param;
2058 slave.setLambdaFromQP(pme.mode.cu, m_rdCost.m_qp);
2059 bool bChroma = slave.m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400;
2060 slave.m_me.setSourcePU(*pme.mode.fencYuv, pme.pu.ctuAddr, pme.pu.cuAbsPartIdx, pme.pu.puAbsPartIdx, pme.pu.width, pme.pu.height, m_param->searchMethod, m_param->subpelRefine, bChroma);
2061 }
2062
2063 /* Perform ME, repeat until no more work is available */
2064 do
2065 {
2066 if (meId < pme.m_jobs.refCnt[0])
2067 {
2068 int refIdx = pme.m_jobs.ref[0][meId]; //L0
2069 slave.singleMotionEstimation(*this, pme.mode, pme.pu, pme.puIdx, 0, refIdx);
2070 }
2071 else
2072 {
2073 int refIdx = pme.m_jobs.ref[1][meId - pme.m_jobs.refCnt[0]]; //L1
2074 slave.singleMotionEstimation(*this, pme.mode, pme.pu, pme.puIdx, 1, refIdx);
2075 }
2076
2077 meId = -1;
2078 pme.m_lock.acquire();
2079 if (pme.m_jobTotal > pme.m_jobAcquired)
2080 meId = pme.m_jobAcquired++;
2081 pme.m_lock.release();
2082 }
2083 while (meId >= 0);
2084}
2085
2086void Search::singleMotionEstimation(Search& master, Mode& interMode, const PredictionUnit& pu, int part, int list, int ref)
2087{
2088 uint32_t bits = master.m_listSelBits[list] + MVP_IDX_BITS;
2089 bits += getTUBits(ref, m_slice->m_numRefIdx[list]);
2090
2091 MotionData* bestME = interMode.bestME[part];
2092
2093 // 12 mv candidates including lowresMV
2094 MV mvc[(MD_ABOVE_LEFT + 1) * 2 + 2];
2095 int numMvc = interMode.cu.getPMV(interMode.interNeighbours, list, ref, interMode.amvpCand[list][ref], mvc);
2096
2097 const MV* amvp = interMode.amvpCand[list][ref];
2098 int mvpIdx = selectMVP(interMode.cu, pu, amvp, list, ref);
2099 bool bLowresMVP = false;
2100 MV mvmin, mvmax, outmv, mvp = amvp[mvpIdx], mvp_lowres;
2101
2102 if (!m_param->analysisSave && !m_param->analysisLoad) /* Prevents load/save outputs from diverging if lowresMV is not available */
2103 {
2104 MV lmv = getLowresMV(interMode.cu, pu, list, ref);
2105 if (lmv.notZero())
2106 mvc[numMvc++] = lmv;
2107 if (m_param->bEnableHME)
2108 mvp_lowres = lmv;
2109 }
2110
2111 setSearchRange(interMode.cu, mvp, m_param->searchRange, mvmin, mvmax);
2112
2113 int satdCost = m_me.motionEstimate(&m_slice->m_mref[list][ref], mvmin, mvmax, mvp, numMvc, mvc, m_param->searchRange, outmv, m_param->maxSlices,
2114 m_param->bSourceReferenceEstimation ? m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_fencPic->getLumaAddr(0) : 0);
2115
2116 if (m_param->bEnableHME && mvp_lowres.notZero() && mvp_lowres != mvp)
2117 {
2118 MV outmv_lowres;
2119 setSearchRange(interMode.cu, mvp_lowres, m_param->searchRange, mvmin, mvmax);
2120 int lowresMvCost = m_me.motionEstimate(&m_slice->m_mref[list][ref], mvmin, mvmax, mvp_lowres, numMvc, mvc, m_param->searchRange, outmv_lowres, m_param->maxSlices,
2121 m_param->bSourceReferenceEstimation ? m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_fencPic->getLumaAddr(0) : 0);
2122 if (lowresMvCost < satdCost)
2123 {
2124 outmv = outmv_lowres;
2125 satdCost = lowresMvCost;
2126 bLowresMVP = true;
2127 }
2128 }
2129 /* Get total cost of partition, but only include MV bit cost once */
2130 bits += m_me.bitcost(outmv);
2131 uint32_t mvCost = m_me.mvcost(outmv);
2132 uint32_t cost = (satdCost - mvCost) + m_rdCost.getCost(bits);
2133
2134 /* Update LowresMVP to best AMVP cand*/
2135 if (bLowresMVP)
2136 updateMVP(amvp[mvpIdx], outmv, bits, cost, mvp_lowres);
2137
2138 /* Refine MVP selection, updates: mvpIdx, bits, cost */
2139 mvp = checkBestMVP(amvp, outmv, mvpIdx, bits, cost);
2140
2141 /* tie goes to the smallest ref ID, just like --no-pme */
2142 ScopedLock _lock(master.m_meLock);
2143 if (cost < bestME[list].cost ||
2144 (cost == bestME[list].cost && ref < bestME[list].ref))
2145 {
2146 bestME[list].mv = outmv;
2147 bestME[list].mvp = mvp;
2148 bestME[list].mvpIdx = mvpIdx;
2149 bestME[list].ref = ref;
2150 bestME[list].cost = cost;
2151 bestME[list].bits = bits;
2152 bestME[list].mvCost = mvCost;
2153 }
2154}
2155void Search::searchMV(Mode& interMode, int list, int ref, MV& outmv, MV mvp[3], int numMvc, MV* mvc)
2156{
2157 CUData& cu = interMode.cu;
2158 MV mv, mvmin, mvmax;
2159 int cand = 0, bestcost = INT_MAX;
2160 while (cand < m_param->mvRefine)
2161 {
2162 if ((cand && mvp[cand] == mvp[cand - 1]) || (cand == 2 && (mvp[cand] == mvp[cand - 2] || mvp[cand] == mvp[cand - 1])))
2163 {
2164 cand++;
2165 continue;
2166 }
2167 MV bestMV;
2168 mv = mvp[cand++];
2169 cu.clipMv(mv);
2170 setSearchRange(cu, mv, m_param->searchRange, mvmin, mvmax);
2171 int cost = m_me.motionEstimate(&m_slice->m_mref[list][ref], mvmin, mvmax, mv, numMvc, mvc, m_param->searchRange, bestMV, m_param->maxSlices,
2172 m_param->bSourceReferenceEstimation ? m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_fencPic->getLumaAddr(0) : 0);
2173 if (bestcost > cost)
2174 {
2175 bestcost = cost;
2176 outmv = bestMV;
2177 }
2178 }
2179}

2181void Search::predInterSearch(Mode& interMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, bool bChromaMC, uint32_t refMasks[2])

2186 Yuv* predYuv = &interMode.predYuv;
2187

2189 MV mvc[(MD_ABOVE_LEFT + 1) * 2 + 2];

2207 useAsMVP = false;

2226 bool bDoUnidir = true;

2228 cu.getNeighbourMV(puIdx, pu.puAbsPartIdx, interMode.interNeighbours);

2230 if ((m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel > 1 && m_param->analysisLoadReuseLevel != 10)

2232 {
2233 for (int list = 0; list < numPredDir; list++)
2234 {
2235
2236 int ref = -1;
2237 if (useAsMVP)
2238 ref = interDataCTU->refIdx[list][cuIdx + puIdx];
2239 else
2240 ref = bestME[list].ref;
2241 if (ref < 0)
2242 {
2243 continue;
2244 }

2246 bits += getTUBits(ref, numRefIdx[list]);
2247

2249 const MV* amvp = interMode.amvpCand[list][ref];
2250 int mvpIdx = selectMVP(cu, pu, amvp, list, ref);
2251 MV mvmin, mvmax, outmv, mvp;

2253 {
2254 mvp = interDataCTU->mv[list][cuIdx + puIdx].word;
2255 mvpIdx = interDataCTU->mvpIdx[list][cuIdx + puIdx];
2256 }
2257 else
2258 mvp = amvp[mvpIdx];
2259 if (m_param->searchMethod == X265_SEA)
2260 {

2265 }

2270 mvpIn = bestME[list].mv;
2271 if (useAsMVP && m_param->mvRefine > 1)
2272 {

2274 int mvpIdxSel[3];
2275 satdCost = m_me.COST_MAX;
2276 mvpSel[0] = mvp;
2277 mvpIdxSel[0] = mvpIdx;

2284 mvpIdxSel[2] = !mvpIdx;

2295 satdCost = bcost;

2298 mvpIdx = mvpIdxSel[cand];
2299 }
2300 }
2301 mvpIn = mvp;
2302 }
2303 else
2304 {

2306 m_param->bSourceReferenceEstimation ? m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_fencPic->getLumaAddr(0) : 0);
2307 }

2310 bits += m_me.bitcost(outmv);
2311 uint32_t mvCost = m_me.mvcost(outmv);
2312 uint32_t cost = (satdCost - mvCost) + m_rdCost.getCost(bits);

2314 if (!(m_param->analysisMultiPassRefine || useAsMVP))

2321 if (diffBits < 0)

2325 bits = origOutBits + diffBits;
2326 cost = (cost - m_rdCost.getCost(origOutBits)) + m_rdCost.getCost(bits);

2328 mvp = amvp[mvpIdx];
2329 }
2330
2331 if (cost < bestME[list].cost)
2332 {
2333 bestME[list].mv = outmv;
2334 bestME[list].mvp = mvp;
2335 bestME[list].mvpIdx = mvpIdx;
2336 bestME[list].cost = cost;

2340 }

2342 }
2343 }
2344 else if (m_param->bDistributeMotionEstimation)
2345 {
2346 PME pme(*this, interMode, cuGeom, pu, puIdx);
2347 pme.m_jobTotal = 0;
2348 pme.m_jobAcquired = 1; /* reserve L0-0 or L1-0 */
2349
2350 uint32_t refMask = refMasks[puIdx] ? refMasks[puIdx] : (uint32_t)-1;
2351 for (int list = 0; list < numPredDir; list++)
2352 {
2353 int idx = 0;
2354 for (int ref = 0; ref < numRefIdx[list]; ref++)
2355 {
2356 if (!(refMask & (1 << ref)))
2357 continue;
2358
2359 pme.m_jobs.ref[list][idx++] = ref;
2360 pme.m_jobTotal++;
2361 }
2362 pme.m_jobs.refCnt[list] = idx;
2363
2364 /* the second list ref bits start at bit 16 */
2365 refMask >>= 16;
2366 }

2370 pme.tryBondPeers(*m_frame->m_encData->m_jobProvider, pme.m_jobTotal - 1);

2373

2378

2380 pme.waitForExit();
2381 }
2382
2383 /* if no peer threads were bonded, fall back to doing unidirectional
2384 * searches ourselves without overhead of singleMotionEstimation() */
2385 }
2386 if (bDoUnidir)
2387 {
2388 interMode.bestME[puIdx][0].ref = interMode.bestME[puIdx][1].ref = -1;
2389 uint32_t refMask = refMasks[puIdx] ? refMasks[puIdx] : (uint32_t)-1;
2390
2391 for (int list = 0; list < numPredDir; list++)
2392 {
2393 for (int ref = 0; ref < numRefIdx[list]; ref++)
2394 {

2396
2397 if (!(refMask & (1 << ref)))
2398 {
2399 ProfileCounter(interMode.cu, skippedMotionReferences[cuGeom.depth]);
2400 continue;
2401 }
2402
2403 uint32_t bits = m_listSelBits[list] + MVP_IDX_BITS;
2404 bits += getTUBits(ref, numRefIdx[list]);
2405

2407
2408 const MV* amvp = interMode.amvpCand[list][ref];
2409 int mvpIdx = selectMVP(cu, pu, amvp, list, ref);
2410 MV mvmin, mvmax, outmv, mvp = amvp[mvpIdx], mvp_lowres;
2411 bool bLowresMVP = false;
2412
2413 if (!m_param->analysisSave && !m_param->analysisLoad) /* Prevents load/save outputs from diverging when lowresMV is not available */
2414 {
2415 MV lmv = getLowresMV(cu, pu, list, ref);
2416 if (lmv.notZero())
2417 mvc[numMvc++] = lmv;
2418 if (m_param->bEnableHME)
2419 mvp_lowres = lmv;
2420 }
2421 if (m_param->searchMethod == X265_SEA)
2422 {
2423 int puX = puIdx & 1;
2424 int puY = puIdx >> 1;
2425 for (int planes = 0; planes < INTEGRAL_PLANE_NUM; planes++)
2426 m_me.integral[planes] = interMode.fencYuv->m_integral[list][ref][planes] + puX * pu.width + puY * pu.height * m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_reconPic->m_stride;
2427 }
2428 setSearchRange(cu, mvp, m_param->searchRange, mvmin, mvmax);
2429 int satdCost = m_me.motionEstimate(&slice->m_mref[list][ref], mvmin, mvmax, mvp, numMvc, mvc, m_param->searchRange, outmv, m_param->maxSlices,
2430 m_param->bSourceReferenceEstimation ? m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_fencPic->getLumaAddr(0) : 0);
2431
2432 if (m_param->bEnableHME && mvp_lowres.notZero() && mvp_lowres != mvp)
2433 {
2434 MV outmv_lowres;
2435 setSearchRange(cu, mvp_lowres, m_param->searchRange, mvmin, mvmax);
2436 int lowresMvCost = m_me.motionEstimate(&slice->m_mref[list][ref], mvmin, mvmax, mvp_lowres, numMvc, mvc, m_param->searchRange, outmv_lowres, m_param->maxSlices,
2437 m_param->bSourceReferenceEstimation ? m_slice->m_refFrameList[list][ref]->m_fencPic->getLumaAddr(0) : 0);
2438 if (lowresMvCost < satdCost)
2439 {
2440 outmv = outmv_lowres;
2441 satdCost = lowresMvCost;
2442 bLowresMVP = true;
2443 }
2444 }
2445
2446 /* Get total cost of partition, but only include MV bit cost once */
2447 bits += m_me.bitcost(outmv);
2448 uint32_t mvCost = m_me.mvcost(outmv);
2449 uint32_t cost = (satdCost - mvCost) + m_rdCost.getCost(bits);
2450 /* Update LowresMVP to best AMVP cand*/
2451 if (bLowresMVP)
2452 updateMVP(amvp[mvpIdx], outmv, bits, cost, mvp_lowres);
2453
2454 /* Refine MVP selection, updates: mvpIdx, bits, cost */
2455 mvp = checkBestMVP(amvp, outmv, mvpIdx, bits, cost);
2456
2457 if (cost < bestME[list].cost)
2458 {
2459 bestME[list].mv = outmv;
2460 bestME[list].mvp = mvp;
2461 bestME[list].mvpIdx = mvpIdx;
2462 bestME[list].ref = ref;
2463 bestME[list].cost = cost;
2464 bestME[list].bits = bits;
2465 bestME[list].mvCost = mvCost;
2466 }
2467 }
2468 /* the second list ref bits start at bit 16 */
2469 refMask >>= 16;
2470 }
2471 }
2472
2473 /* Bi-directional prediction */
2474 MotionData bidir[2];
2475 uint32_t bidirCost = MAX_UINT;
2476 int bidirBits = 0;
2477
2478 if (slice->isInterB() && !cu.isBipredRestriction() && /* biprediction is possible for this PU */
2479 cu.m_partSize[pu.puAbsPartIdx] != SIZE_2Nx2N && /* 2Nx2N biprediction is handled elsewhere */
2480 bestME[0].cost != MAX_UINT && bestME[1].cost != MAX_UINT)
2481 {
2482 bidir[0] = bestME[0];
2483 bidir[1] = bestME[1];
2484
2485 int satdCost;
2486
2487 if (m_me.bChromaSATD)
2488 {
2489 cu.m_mv[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bidir[0].mv;
2490 cu.m_refIdx[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = (int8_t)bidir[0].ref;
2491 cu.m_mv[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bidir[1].mv;
2492 cu.m_refIdx[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = (int8_t)bidir[1].ref;
2493 motionCompensation(cu, pu, tmpPredYuv, true, true);
2494
2495 satdCost = m_me.bufSATD(tmpPredYuv.getLumaAddr(pu.puAbsPartIdx), tmpPredYuv.m_size) +
2496 m_me.bufChromaSATD(tmpPredYuv, pu.puAbsPartIdx);
2497 }
2498 else
2499 {
2500 PicYuv* refPic0 = slice->m_refReconPicList[0][bestME[0].ref];
2501 PicYuv* refPic1 = slice->m_refReconPicList[1][bestME[1].ref];
2502 Yuv* bidirYuv = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].bidirPredYuv;
2503
2504 /* Generate reference subpels */
2505 predInterLumaPixel(pu, bidirYuv[0], *refPic0, bestME[0].mv);
2506 predInterLumaPixel(pu, bidirYuv[1], *refPic1, bestME[1].mv);
2507 primitives.pu[m_me.partEnum].pixelavg_pp[(tmpPredYuv.m_size % 64 == 0) && (bidirYuv[0].m_size % 64 == 0) && (bidirYuv[1].m_size % 64 == 0)](tmpPredYuv.m_buf[0], tmpPredYuv.m_size, bidirYuv[0].getLumaAddr(pu.puAbsPartIdx), bidirYuv[0].m_size,
2508 bidirYuv[1].getLumaAddr(pu.puAbsPartIdx), bidirYuv[1].m_size, 32);
2509 satdCost = m_me.bufSATD(tmpPredYuv.m_buf[0], tmpPredYuv.m_size);
2510 }
2511
2512 bidirBits = bestME[0].bits + bestME[1].bits + m_listSelBits[2] - (m_listSelBits[0] + m_listSelBits[1]);
2513 bidirCost = satdCost + m_rdCost.getCost(bidirBits);
2514
2515 bool bTryZero = bestME[0].mv.notZero() || bestME[1].mv.notZero();
2516 if (bTryZero)
2517 {
2518 /* Do not try zero MV if unidir motion predictors are beyond
2519 * valid search area */
2520 MV mvmin, mvmax;
2521 int merange = X265_MAX(m_param->sourceWidth, m_param->sourceHeight);
2522 setSearchRange(cu, mvzero, merange, mvmin, mvmax);
2523 mvmax.y += 2; // there is some pad for subpel refine
2524 mvmin <<= 2;
2525 mvmax <<= 2;
2526
2527 bTryZero &= bestME[0].mvp.checkRange(mvmin, mvmax);
2528 bTryZero &= bestME[1].mvp.checkRange(mvmin, mvmax);
2529 }
2530 if (bTryZero)
2531 {
2532 /* coincident blocks of the two reference pictures */
2533 if (m_me.bChromaSATD)
2534 {
2535 cu.m_mv[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = mvzero;
2536 cu.m_refIdx[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = (int8_t)bidir[0].ref;
2537 cu.m_mv[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = mvzero;
2538 cu.m_refIdx[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = (int8_t)bidir[1].ref;
2539 motionCompensation(cu, pu, tmpPredYuv, true, true);
2540
2541 satdCost = m_me.bufSATD(tmpPredYuv.getLumaAddr(pu.puAbsPartIdx), tmpPredYuv.m_size) +
2542 m_me.bufChromaSATD(tmpPredYuv, pu.puAbsPartIdx);
2543 }
2544 else
2545 {
2546 const pixel* ref0 = m_slice->m_mref[0][bestME[0].ref].getLumaAddr(pu.ctuAddr, pu.cuAbsPartIdx + pu.puAbsPartIdx);
2547 const pixel* ref1 = m_slice->m_mref[1][bestME[1].ref].getLumaAddr(pu.ctuAddr, pu.cuAbsPartIdx + pu.puAbsPartIdx);
2548 intptr_t refStride = slice->m_mref[0][0].lumaStride;
2549 primitives.pu[m_me.partEnum].pixelavg_pp[(tmpPredYuv.m_size % 64 == 0) && (refStride % 64 == 0)](tmpPredYuv.m_buf[0], tmpPredYuv.m_size, ref0, refStride, ref1, refStride, 32);
2550 satdCost = m_me.bufSATD(tmpPredYuv.m_buf[0], tmpPredYuv.m_size);
2551 }
2552 MV mvp0 = bestME[0].mvp;
2553 int mvpIdx0 = bestME[0].mvpIdx;
2554 uint32_t bits0 = bestME[0].bits - m_me.bitcost(bestME[0].mv, mvp0) + m_me.bitcost(mvzero, mvp0);
2555
2556 MV mvp1 = bestME[1].mvp;
2557 int mvpIdx1 = bestME[1].mvpIdx;
2558 uint32_t bits1 = bestME[1].bits - m_me.bitcost(bestME[1].mv, mvp1) + m_me.bitcost(mvzero, mvp1);
2559
2560 uint32_t cost = satdCost + m_rdCost.getCost(bits0) + m_rdCost.getCost(bits1);
2561
2562 /* refine MVP selection for zero mv, updates: mvp, mvpidx, bits, cost */
2563 mvp0 = checkBestMVP(interMode.amvpCand[0][bestME[0].ref], mvzero, mvpIdx0, bits0, cost);
2564 mvp1 = checkBestMVP(interMode.amvpCand[1][bestME[1].ref], mvzero, mvpIdx1, bits1, cost);
2565
2566 if (cost < bidirCost)
2567 {
2568 bidir[0].mv = mvzero;
2569 bidir[1].mv = mvzero;
2570 bidir[0].mvp = mvp0;
2571 bidir[1].mvp = mvp1;
2572 bidir[0].mvpIdx = mvpIdx0;
2573 bidir[1].mvpIdx = mvpIdx1;
2574 bidirCost = cost;
2575 bidirBits = bits0 + bits1 + m_listSelBits[2] - (m_listSelBits[0] + m_listSelBits[1]);
2576 }
2577 }
2578 }
2579
2580 /* select best option and store into CU */
2581 if (mrgCost < bidirCost && mrgCost < bestME[0].cost && mrgCost < bestME[1].cost)
2582 {
2583 cu.m_mergeFlag[pu.puAbsPartIdx] = true;
2584 cu.m_mvpIdx[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = merge.index; /* merge candidate ID is stored in L0 MVP idx */
2585 cu.setPUInterDir(merge.dir, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2586 cu.setPUMv(0, merge.mvField[0].mv, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2587 cu.setPURefIdx(0, merge.mvField[0].refIdx, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2588 cu.setPUMv(1, merge.mvField[1].mv, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2589 cu.setPURefIdx(1, merge.mvField[1].refIdx, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2590
2591 totalmebits += merge.bits;
2592 }
2593 else if (bidirCost < bestME[0].cost && bidirCost < bestME[1].cost)
2594 {
2595 lastMode = 2;
2596
2597 cu.m_mergeFlag[pu.puAbsPartIdx] = false;
2598 cu.setPUInterDir(3, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2599 cu.setPUMv(0, bidir[0].mv, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2600 cu.setPURefIdx(0, bestME[0].ref, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2601 cu.m_mvd[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bidir[0].mv - bidir[0].mvp;
2602 cu.m_mvpIdx[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bidir[0].mvpIdx;
2603
2604 cu.setPUMv(1, bidir[1].mv, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2605 cu.setPURefIdx(1, bestME[1].ref, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2606 cu.m_mvd[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bidir[1].mv - bidir[1].mvp;
2607 cu.m_mvpIdx[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bidir[1].mvpIdx;
2608
2609 totalmebits += bidirBits;
2610 }
2611 else if (bestME[0].cost <= bestME[1].cost)
2612 {
2613 lastMode = 0;
2614
2615 cu.m_mergeFlag[pu.puAbsPartIdx] = false;
2616 cu.setPUInterDir(1, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2617 cu.setPUMv(0, bestME[0].mv, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2618 cu.setPURefIdx(0, bestME[0].ref, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2619 cu.m_mvd[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bestME[0].mv - bestME[0].mvp;
2620 cu.m_mvpIdx[0][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bestME[0].mvpIdx;
2621
2622 cu.setPURefIdx(1, REF_NOT_VALID, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2623 cu.setPUMv(1, mvzero, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2624
2625 totalmebits += bestME[0].bits;
2626 }
2627 else
2628 {
2629 lastMode = 1;
2630
2631 cu.m_mergeFlag[pu.puAbsPartIdx] = false;
2632 cu.setPUInterDir(2, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2633 cu.setPUMv(1, bestME[1].mv, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2634 cu.setPURefIdx(1, bestME[1].ref, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2635 cu.m_mvd[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bestME[1].mv - bestME[1].mvp;
2636 cu.m_mvpIdx[1][pu.puAbsPartIdx] = bestME[1].mvpIdx;
2637
2638 cu.setPURefIdx(0, REF_NOT_VALID, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2639 cu.setPUMv(0, mvzero, pu.puAbsPartIdx, puIdx);
2640
2641 totalmebits += bestME[1].bits;
2642 }
2643
2644 motionCompensation(cu, pu, *predYuv, true, bChromaMC);
2645 }
2646 interMode.sa8dBits += totalmebits;
2647}
2648
2649void Search::getBlkBits(PartSize cuMode, bool bPSlice, int partIdx, uint32_t lastMode, uint32_t blockBit[3])
2650{
2651 if (cuMode == SIZE_2Nx2N)
2652 {
2653 blockBit[0] = (!bPSlice) ? 3 : 1;
2654 blockBit[1] = 3;
2655 blockBit[2] = 5;
2656 }
2657 else if (cuMode == SIZE_2NxN || cuMode == SIZE_2NxnU || cuMode == SIZE_2NxnD)
2658 {
2659 static const uint32_t listBits[2][3][3] =
2660 {
2661 { { 0, 0, 3 }, { 0, 0, 0 }, { 0, 0, 0 } },
2662 { { 5, 7, 7 }, { 7, 5, 7 }, { 9 - 3, 9 - 3, 9 - 3 } }
2663 };
2664 if (bPSlice)
2665 {
2666 blockBit[0] = 3;
2667 blockBit[1] = 0;
2668 blockBit[2] = 0;
2669 }
2670 else
2671 memcpy(blockBit, listBits[partIdx][lastMode], 3 * sizeof(uint32_t));
2672 }
2673 else if (cuMode == SIZE_Nx2N || cuMode == SIZE_nLx2N || cuMode == SIZE_nRx2N)
2674 {
2675 static const uint32_t listBits[2][3][3] =
2676 {
2677 { { 0, 2, 3 }, { 0, 0, 0 }, { 0, 0, 0 } },
2678 { { 5, 7, 7 }, { 7 - 2, 7 - 2, 9 - 2 }, { 9 - 3, 9 - 3, 9 - 3 } }
2679 };
2680 if (bPSlice)
2681 {
2682 blockBit[0] = 3;
2683 blockBit[1] = 0;
2684 blockBit[2] = 0;
2685 }
2686 else
2687 memcpy(blockBit, listBits[partIdx][lastMode], 3 * sizeof(uint32_t));
2688 }
2689 else if (cuMode == SIZE_NxN)
2690 {
2691 blockBit[0] = (!bPSlice) ? 3 : 1;
2692 blockBit[1] = 3;
2693 blockBit[2] = 5;
2694 }
2695 else
2696 {
2697 X265_CHECK(0, "getBlkBits: unknown cuMode\n");
2698 }
2699}
2700
2701/* Check if using an alternative MVP would result in a smaller MVD + signal bits */
2702const MV& Search::checkBestMVP(const MV* amvpCand, const MV& mv, int& mvpIdx, uint32_t& outBits, uint32_t& outCost) const
2703{
2704 int diffBits = m_me.bitcost(mv, amvpCand[!mvpIdx]) - m_me.bitcost(mv, amvpCand[mvpIdx]);
2705 if (diffBits < 0)
2706 {
2707 mvpIdx = !mvpIdx;
2708 uint32_t origOutBits = outBits;
2709 outBits = origOutBits + diffBits;
2710 outCost = (outCost - m_rdCost.getCost(origOutBits)) + m_rdCost.getCost(outBits);
2711 }
2712 return amvpCand[mvpIdx];
2713}
2714
2715/* Update to default MVP when using an alternative mvp */
2716void Search::updateMVP(const MV amvp, const MV& mv, uint32_t& outBits, uint32_t& outCost, const MV& alterMVP)
2717{
2718 int diffBits = m_me.bitcost(mv, amvp) - m_me.bitcost(mv, alterMVP);
2719 uint32_t origOutBits = outBits;
2720 outBits = origOutBits + diffBits;
2721 outCost = (outCost - m_rdCost.getCost(origOutBits)) + m_rdCost.getCost(outBits);
2722}
2723
2724void Search::setSearchRange(const CUData& cu, const MV& mvp, int merange, MV& mvmin, MV& mvmax) const
2725{
2726 MV dist((int32_t)merange << 2, (int32_t)merange << 2);
2727 mvmin = mvp - dist;
2728 mvmax = mvp + dist;
2729
2730 cu.clipMv(mvmin);
2731 cu.clipMv(mvmax);
2732
2733 if (cu.m_encData->m_param->bIntraRefresh && m_slice->m_sliceType == P_SLICE &&
2734 cu.m_cuPelX / m_param->maxCUSize < m_frame->m_encData->m_pir.pirStartCol &&
2735 m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][0]->m_encData->m_pir.pirEndCol < m_slice->m_sps->numCuInWidth)
2736 {
2737 int safeX, maxSafeMv;
2738 safeX = m_slice->m_refFrameList[0][0]->m_encData->m_pir.pirEndCol * m_param->maxCUSize - 3;
2739 maxSafeMv = (safeX - cu.m_cuPelX) * 4;
2740 mvmax.x = X265_MIN(mvmax.x, maxSafeMv);
2741 mvmin.x = X265_MIN(mvmin.x, maxSafeMv);
2742 }
2743
2744 // apply restrict on slices
2745 if ((m_param->maxSlices > 1) & m_bFrameParallel)
2746 {
2747 mvmin.y = X265_MAX(mvmin.y, m_sliceMinY);
2748 mvmax.y = X265_MIN(mvmax.y, m_sliceMaxY);
2749 }
2750
2751 /* Clip search range to signaled maximum MV length.
2752 * We do not support this VUI field being changed from the default */
2753 const int maxMvLen = (1 << 15) - 1;
2754 mvmin.x = X265_MAX(mvmin.x, -maxMvLen);
2755 mvmin.y = X265_MAX(mvmin.y, -maxMvLen);
2756 mvmax.x = X265_MIN(mvmax.x, maxMvLen);
2757 mvmax.y = X265_MIN(mvmax.y, maxMvLen);
2758
2759 mvmin >>= 2;
2760 mvmax >>= 2;
2761
2762 /* conditional clipping for frame parallelism */
2763 mvmin.y = X265_MIN(mvmin.y, (int32_t)m_refLagPixels);
2764 mvmax.y = X265_MIN(mvmax.y, (int32_t)m_refLagPixels);
2765
2766 /* conditional clipping for negative mv range */
2767 mvmax.y = X265_MAX(mvmax.y, mvmin.y);
2768}

2770/* Note: this function overwrites the RD cost variables of interMode, but leaves the sa8d cost unharmed */
2771void Search::encodeResAndCalcRdSkipCU(Mode& interMode)
2772{
2773 CUData& cu = interMode.cu;
2774 Yuv* reconYuv = &interMode.reconYuv;
2775 const Yuv* fencYuv = interMode.fencYuv;
2776 Yuv* predYuv = &interMode.predYuv;
2777 X265_CHECK(!cu.isIntra(0), "intra CU not expected\n");
2778 uint32_t depth = cu.m_cuDepth[0];
2779
2780 // No residual coding : SKIP mode
2781
2782 cu.setPredModeSubParts(MODE_SKIP);
2783 cu.clearCbf();
2784 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(0, 0, depth);
2785
2786 reconYuv->copyFromYuv(interMode.predYuv);
2787
2788 // Luma
2789 int part = partitionFromLog2Size(cu.m_log2CUSize[0]);
2790 interMode.lumaDistortion = primitives.cu[part].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size);
2791 interMode.distortion = interMode.lumaDistortion;
2792 // Chroma
2793 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
2794 {
2795 interMode.chromaDistortion = m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(1, primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[part].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[1], fencYuv->m_csize, reconYuv->m_buf[1], reconYuv->m_csize));
2796 interMode.chromaDistortion += m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(2, primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[part].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[2], fencYuv->m_csize, reconYuv->m_buf[2], reconYuv->m_csize));
2797 interMode.distortion += interMode.chromaDistortion;
2798 }
2799 cu.m_distortion[0] = interMode.distortion;
2800 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
2801 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
2802 if (m_slice->m_pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled)
2803 m_entropyCoder.codeCUTransquantBypassFlag(cu.m_tqBypass[0]);
2804 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
2805 int skipFlagBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
2806 m_entropyCoder.codeMergeIndex(cu, 0);
2807 interMode.mvBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits() - skipFlagBits;
2808 interMode.coeffBits = 0;
2809 interMode.totalBits = interMode.mvBits + skipFlagBits;
2810 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
2811 interMode.psyEnergy = m_rdCost.psyCost(part, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size);
2812 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
2813 interMode.ssimEnergy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size, cu.m_log2CUSize[0], TEXT_LUMA, 0);
2814
2815 interMode.resEnergy = primitives.cu[part].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, predYuv->m_buf[0], predYuv->m_size);
2816 updateModeCost(interMode);
2817 m_entropyCoder.store(interMode.contexts);
2818}
2819
2820/* encode residual and calculate rate-distortion for a CU block.
2821 * Note: this function overwrites the RD cost variables of interMode, but leaves the sa8d cost unharmed */
2822void Search::encodeResAndCalcRdInterCU(Mode& interMode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
2823{
2824 ProfileCUScope(interMode.cu, interRDOElapsedTime[cuGeom.depth], countInterRDO[cuGeom.depth]);
2825
2826 CUData& cu = interMode.cu;
2827 Yuv* reconYuv = &interMode.reconYuv;
2828 Yuv* predYuv = &interMode.predYuv;
2829 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth;
2830 ShortYuv* resiYuv = &m_rqt[depth].tmpResiYuv;
2831 const Yuv* fencYuv = interMode.fencYuv;
2832
2833 X265_CHECK(!cu.isIntra(0), "intra CU not expected\n");
2834
2835 uint32_t log2CUSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize;
2836 int sizeIdx = log2CUSize - 2;
2837
2838 resiYuv->subtract(*fencYuv, *predYuv, log2CUSize, m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp);
2839
2840 uint32_t tuDepthRange[2];
2841 cu.getInterTUQtDepthRange(tuDepthRange, 0);
2842
2843 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
2844
2845 if ((m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_DFS) && !(m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_NEIGH))
2846 m_maxTUDepth = -1;
2847 else if (m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_BFS)
2848 memset(&m_cacheTU, 0, sizeof(TUInfoCache));
2849
2850 Cost costs;
2851 if (m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_NEIGH)
2852 {
2853 /* Save and reload maxTUDepth to avoid changing of maxTUDepth between modes */
2854 int32_t tempDepth = m_maxTUDepth;
2855 if (m_maxTUDepth != -1)
2856 {
2857 uint32_t splitFlag = interMode.cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N;
2858 uint32_t minSize = tuDepthRange[0];
2859 uint32_t maxSize = tuDepthRange[1];
2860 maxSize = X265_MIN(maxSize, cuGeom.log2CUSize - splitFlag);
2861 m_maxTUDepth = x265_clip3(cuGeom.log2CUSize - maxSize, cuGeom.log2CUSize - minSize, (uint32_t)m_maxTUDepth);
2862 }
2863 estimateResidualQT(interMode, cuGeom, 0, 0, *resiYuv, costs, tuDepthRange);
2864 m_maxTUDepth = tempDepth;
2865 }
2866 else
2867 estimateResidualQT(interMode, cuGeom, 0, 0, *resiYuv, costs, tuDepthRange);
2868
2869 uint32_t tqBypass = cu.m_tqBypass[0];
2870 if (!tqBypass)
2871 {
2872 sse_t cbf0Dist = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, predYuv->m_buf[0], predYuv->m_size);
2873 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
2874 {
2875 cbf0Dist += m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(1, primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[1], predYuv->m_csize, predYuv->m_buf[1], predYuv->m_csize));
2876 cbf0Dist += m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(2, primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[2], predYuv->m_csize, predYuv->m_buf[2], predYuv->m_csize));
2877 }
2878
2879 /* Consider the RD cost of not signaling any residual */
2880 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
2881 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
2882 m_entropyCoder.codeQtRootCbfZero();
2883 uint32_t cbf0Bits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
2884
2885 uint32_t cbf0Energy; uint64_t cbf0Cost;
2886 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
2887 {
2888 cbf0Energy = m_rdCost.psyCost(log2CUSize - 2, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, predYuv->m_buf[0], predYuv->m_size);
2889 cbf0Cost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(cbf0Dist, cbf0Bits, cbf0Energy);
2890 }
2891 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
2892 {
2893 cbf0Energy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, predYuv->m_buf[0], predYuv->m_size, log2CUSize, TEXT_LUMA, 0);
2894 cbf0Cost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(cbf0Dist, cbf0Bits, cbf0Energy);
2895 }
2896 else
2897 cbf0Cost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(cbf0Dist, cbf0Bits);
2898
2899 if (cbf0Cost < costs.rdcost)
2900 {
2901 cu.clearCbf();
2902 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(0, 0, depth);
2903 }
2904 }
2905
2906 if (cu.getQtRootCbf(0))
2907 saveResidualQTData(cu, *resiYuv, 0, 0);
2908
2909 /* calculate signal bits for inter/merge/skip coded CU */
2910 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].cur);
2911
2912 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
2913 if (m_slice->m_pps->bTransquantBypassEnabled)
2914 m_entropyCoder.codeCUTransquantBypassFlag(tqBypass);
2915
2916 uint32_t coeffBits, bits, mvBits;
2917 if (cu.m_mergeFlag[0] && cu.m_partSize[0] == SIZE_2Nx2N && !cu.getQtRootCbf(0))
2918 {
2919 cu.setPredModeSubParts(MODE_SKIP);
2920
2921 /* Merge/Skip */
2922 coeffBits = mvBits = 0;
2923 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
2924 int skipFlagBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
2925 m_entropyCoder.codeMergeIndex(cu, 0);
2926 mvBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits() - skipFlagBits;
2927 bits = mvBits + skipFlagBits;
2928 }
2929 else
2930 {
2931 m_entropyCoder.codeSkipFlag(cu, 0);
2932 int skipFlagBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
2933 m_entropyCoder.codePredMode(cu.m_predMode[0]);
2934 m_entropyCoder.codePartSize(cu, 0, cuGeom.depth);
2935 m_entropyCoder.codePredInfo(cu, 0);
2936 mvBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits() - skipFlagBits;
2937
2938 bool bCodeDQP = m_slice->m_pps->bUseDQP;
2939 m_entropyCoder.codeCoeff(cu, 0, bCodeDQP, tuDepthRange);
2940 bits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
2941
2942 coeffBits = bits - mvBits - skipFlagBits;
2943 }
2944
2945 m_entropyCoder.store(interMode.contexts);
2946
2947 if (cu.getQtRootCbf(0))
2948 reconYuv->addClip(*predYuv, *resiYuv, log2CUSize, m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp);
2949 else
2950 reconYuv->copyFromYuv(*predYuv);
2951
2952 // update with clipped distortion and cost (qp estimation loop uses unclipped values)
2953 sse_t bestLumaDist = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size);
2954 interMode.distortion = bestLumaDist;
2955 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
2956 {
2957 sse_t bestChromaDist = m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(1, primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[1], fencYuv->m_csize, reconYuv->m_buf[1], reconYuv->m_csize));
2958 bestChromaDist += m_rdCost.scaleChromaDist(2, primitives.chroma[m_csp].cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[2], fencYuv->m_csize, reconYuv->m_buf[2], reconYuv->m_csize));
2959 interMode.chromaDistortion = bestChromaDist;
2960 interMode.distortion += bestChromaDist;
2961 }
2962 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
2963 interMode.psyEnergy = m_rdCost.psyCost(sizeIdx, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size);
2964 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
2965 interMode.ssimEnergy = m_quant.ssimDistortion(cu, fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, reconYuv->m_buf[0], reconYuv->m_size, cu.m_log2CUSize[0], TEXT_LUMA, 0);
2966
2967 interMode.resEnergy = primitives.cu[sizeIdx].sse_pp(fencYuv->m_buf[0], fencYuv->m_size, predYuv->m_buf[0], predYuv->m_size);
2968 interMode.totalBits = bits;
2969 interMode.lumaDistortion = bestLumaDist;
2970 interMode.coeffBits = coeffBits;
2971 interMode.mvBits = mvBits;
2972 cu.m_distortion[0] = interMode.distortion;
2973 updateModeCost(interMode);
2974 checkDQP(interMode, cuGeom);
2975}

2977void Search::residualTransformQuantInter(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth, const uint32_t depthRange[2])
2978{
2979 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
2980 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
2981 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
2982
2983 bool bCheckFull = log2TrSize <= depthRange[1];
2984 if (cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N && !tuDepth && log2TrSize > depthRange[0])
2985 bCheckFull = false;
2986
2987 if (bCheckFull)
2988 {
2989 // code full block
2990 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
2991 uint32_t codeChroma = (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400) ? 1 : 0;
2992
2993 uint32_t tuDepthC = tuDepth;
2994 if (log2TrSizeC < 2)
2995 {
2996 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize == 2 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
2997 log2TrSizeC = 2;
2998 tuDepthC--;
2999 codeChroma &= !(absPartIdx & 3);
3000 }
3001
3002 uint32_t absPartIdxStep = cuGeom.numPartitions >> tuDepthC * 2;
3003 uint32_t setCbf = 1 << tuDepth;
3004
3005 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2);
3006 coeff_t* coeffCurY = cu.m_trCoeff[0] + coeffOffsetY;
3007
3008 uint32_t sizeIdx = log2TrSize - 2;
3009
3010 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(tuDepth, absPartIdx, depth);
3011 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(0, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, depth);
3012
3013 ShortYuv& resiYuv = m_rqt[cuGeom.depth].tmpResiYuv;
3014 const Yuv* fencYuv = mode.fencYuv;
3015
3016 int16_t* curResiY = resiYuv.getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
3017 uint32_t strideResiY = resiYuv.m_size;
3018
3019 const pixel* fenc = fencYuv->getLumaAddr(absPartIdx);
3020 uint32_t numSigY = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fenc, fencYuv->m_size, curResiY, strideResiY, coeffCurY, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, false);
3021
3022 if (numSigY)
3023 {
3024 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, curResiY, strideResiY, coeffCurY, log2TrSize, TEXT_LUMA, false, false, numSigY);
3025 cu.setCbfSubParts(setCbf, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, depth);
3026 }
3027 else
3028 {
3029 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].blockfill_s[strideResiY % 64 == 0](curResiY, strideResiY, 0);
3030 cu.setCbfSubParts(0, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, depth);
3031 }
3032
3033 if (codeChroma)
3034 {
3035 uint32_t sizeIdxC = log2TrSizeC - 2;
3036 uint32_t strideResiC = resiYuv.m_csize;
3037
3038 uint32_t coeffOffsetC = coeffOffsetY >> (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift);
3039 coeff_t* coeffCurU = cu.m_trCoeff[1] + coeffOffsetC;
3040 coeff_t* coeffCurV = cu.m_trCoeff[2] + coeffOffsetC;
3041 bool splitIntoSubTUs = (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422);
3042
3043 TURecurse tuIterator(splitIntoSubTUs ? VERTICAL_SPLIT : DONT_SPLIT, absPartIdxStep, absPartIdx);
3044 do
3045 {
3046 uint32_t absPartIdxC = tuIterator.absPartIdxTURelCU;
3047 uint32_t subTUOffset = tuIterator.section << (log2TrSizeC * 2);
3048
3049 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(0, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3050 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(0, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3051
3052 int16_t* curResiU = resiYuv.getCbAddr(absPartIdxC);
3053 const pixel* fencCb = fencYuv->getCbAddr(absPartIdxC);
3054 uint32_t numSigU = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fencCb, fencYuv->m_csize, curResiU, strideResiC, coeffCurU + subTUOffset, log2TrSizeC, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdxC, false);
3055 if (numSigU)
3056 {
3057 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, curResiU, strideResiC, coeffCurU + subTUOffset, log2TrSizeC, TEXT_CHROMA_U, false, false, numSigU);
3058 cu.setCbfPartRange(setCbf, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3059 }
3060 else
3061 {
3062 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].blockfill_s[strideResiC % 64 == 0](curResiU, strideResiC, 0);
3063 cu.setCbfPartRange(0, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3064 }
3065
3066 int16_t* curResiV = resiYuv.getCrAddr(absPartIdxC);
3067 const pixel* fencCr = fencYuv->getCrAddr(absPartIdxC);
3068 uint32_t numSigV = m_quant.transformNxN(cu, fencCr, fencYuv->m_csize, curResiV, strideResiC, coeffCurV + subTUOffset, log2TrSizeC, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdxC, false);
3069 if (numSigV)
3070 {
3071 m_quant.invtransformNxN(cu, curResiV, strideResiC, coeffCurV + subTUOffset, log2TrSizeC, TEXT_CHROMA_V, false, false, numSigV);
3072 cu.setCbfPartRange(setCbf, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3073 }
3074 else
3075 {
3076 primitives.cu[sizeIdxC].blockfill_s[strideResiC % 64 == 0](curResiV, strideResiC, 0);
3077 cu.setCbfPartRange(0, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3078 }
3079 }
3080 while (tuIterator.isNextSection());
3081
3082 if (splitIntoSubTUs)
3083 {
3084 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
3085 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
3086 }
3087 }
3088 }
3089 else
3090 {
3091 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize > depthRange[0], "residualTransformQuantInter recursion check failure\n");
3092
3093 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
3094 uint32_t ycbf = 0, ucbf = 0, vcbf = 0;
3095 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = absPartIdx; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
3096 {
3097 residualTransformQuantInter(mode, cuGeom, qPartIdx, tuDepth + 1, depthRange);
3098 ycbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth + 1);
3099 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
3100 {
3101 ucbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth + 1);
3102 vcbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth + 1);
3103 }
3104 }
3105 cu.m_cbf[0][absPartIdx] |= ycbf << tuDepth;
3106 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
3107 {
3108 cu.m_cbf[1][absPartIdx] |= ucbf << tuDepth;
3109 cu.m_cbf[2][absPartIdx] |= vcbf << tuDepth;
3110 }
3111 }
3112}

3114uint64_t Search::estimateNullCbfCost(sse_t dist, uint32_t energy, uint32_t tuDepth, TextType compId)
3115{
3116 uint32_t nullBits = m_entropyCoder.estimateCbfBits(0, compId, tuDepth);
3117
3118 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
3119 return m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(dist, nullBits, energy);
3120 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)

3122 else

3125
3126bool Search::splitTU(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth, ShortYuv& resiYuv, Cost& splitCost, const uint32_t depthRange[2], int32_t splitMore)
3127{
3128 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
3129 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
3130 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
3131
3132 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
3133 uint32_t ycbf = 0, ucbf = 0, vcbf = 0;
3134 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0, qPartIdx = absPartIdx; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, qPartIdx += qNumParts)
3135 {
3136 if ((m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_DFS) && tuDepth == 0 && qIdx == 1)
3137 {
3138 m_maxTUDepth = cu.m_tuDepth[0];
3139 // Fetch maximum TU depth of first sub partition to limit recursion of others
3140 for (uint32_t i = 1; i < cuGeom.numPartitions / 4; i++)
3141 m_maxTUDepth = X265_MAX(m_maxTUDepth, cu.m_tuDepth[i]);
3142 }
3143 estimateResidualQT(mode, cuGeom, qPartIdx, tuDepth + 1, resiYuv, splitCost, depthRange, splitMore);
3144 ycbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth + 1);
3145 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
3146 {
3147 ucbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth + 1);
3148 vcbf |= cu.getCbf(qPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth + 1);
3149 }
3150 }
3151 cu.m_cbf[0][absPartIdx] |= ycbf << tuDepth;
3152 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
3153 {
3154 cu.m_cbf[1][absPartIdx] |= ucbf << tuDepth;
3155 cu.m_cbf[2][absPartIdx] |= vcbf << tuDepth;
3156 }
3157
3158 // Here we were encoding cbfs and coefficients for splitted blocks. Since I have collected coefficient bits
3159 // for each individual blocks, only encoding cbf values. As I mentioned encoding chroma cbfs is different then luma.
3160 // But have one doubt that if coefficients are encoded in context at depth 2 (for example) and cbfs are encoded in context
3161 // at depth 0 (for example).
3162 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].rqtRoot);
3163 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
3164 codeInterSubdivCbfQT(cu, absPartIdx, tuDepth, depthRange);
3165 uint32_t splitCbfBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
3166 splitCost.bits += splitCbfBits;
3167
3168 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
3169 splitCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(splitCost.distortion, splitCost.bits, splitCost.energy);
3170 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
3171 splitCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(splitCost.distortion, splitCost.bits, splitCost.energy);
3172 else
3173 splitCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(splitCost.distortion, splitCost.bits);
3174
3175 return ycbf || ucbf || vcbf;
3176}
3177
3178void Search::estimateResidualQT(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth, ShortYuv& resiYuv, Cost& outCosts, const uint32_t depthRange[2], int32_t splitMore)
3179{
3180 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
3181 uint32_t depth = cuGeom.depth + tuDepth;
3182 uint32_t log2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - tuDepth;
3183 bool bEnableRDOQ = !!m_param->rdoqLevel;
3184
3185 bool bCheckSplit = log2TrSize > depthRange[0];
3186 bool bCheckFull = log2TrSize <= depthRange[1];
3187 bool bSaveTUData = false, bLoadTUData = false;
3188 uint32_t idx = 0;
3189
3190 if ((m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_BFS) && splitMore >= 0)
3191 {
3192 if (bCheckSplit && bCheckFull && tuDepth)
3193 {
3194 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
3195 uint32_t qIdx = (absPartIdx / qNumParts) % 4;
3196 idx = (depth - 1) * 4 + qIdx;
3197 if (splitMore)
3198 {
3199 bLoadTUData = true;
3200 bCheckFull = false;
3201 }
3202 else
3203 {
3204 bSaveTUData = true;
3205 bCheckSplit = false;
3206 }
3207 }
3208 }
3209 else if (m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_DFS || m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_NEIGH)
3210 {
3211 if (bCheckSplit && m_maxTUDepth >= 0)
3212 {
3213 uint32_t log2MaxTrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - m_maxTUDepth;
3214 bCheckSplit = log2TrSize > log2MaxTrSize;
3215 }
3216 }
3217
3218 bool bSplitPresentFlag = bCheckSplit && bCheckFull;
3219
3220 if (cu.m_partSize[0] != SIZE_2Nx2N && !tuDepth && bCheckSplit)
3221 bCheckFull = false;
3222
3223 X265_CHECK(bCheckFull || bCheckSplit, "check-full or check-split must be set\n");
3224
3225 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
3226 uint32_t codeChroma = (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400) ? 1 : 0;
3227 uint32_t tuDepthC = tuDepth;
3228 if (log2TrSizeC < 2)
3229 {
3230 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize == 2 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
3231 log2TrSizeC = 2;
3232 tuDepthC--;
3233 codeChroma &= !(absPartIdx & 3);
3234 }
3235
3236 // code full block
3237 Cost fullCost;
3238 fullCost.rdcost = MAX_INT64;
3239
3240 uint8_t cbfFlag[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { 0, 0 }, {0, 0}, {0, 0} };
3241 uint32_t numSig[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { 0, 0 }, {0, 0}, {0, 0} };
3242 uint32_t singleBits[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 } };
3243 sse_t singleDist[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 } };
3244 uint32_t singleEnergy[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 } };
3245 uint32_t bestTransformMode[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 }, { 0, 0 } };
3246 uint64_t minCost[MAX_NUM_COMPONENT][2 /*0 = top (or whole TU for non-4:2:2) sub-TU, 1 = bottom sub-TU*/] = { { MAX_INT64, MAX_INT64 }, {MAX_INT64, MAX_INT64}, {MAX_INT64, MAX_INT64} };
3247
3248 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[depth].rqtRoot);
3249
3250 uint32_t trSize = 1 << log2TrSize;
3251 const bool splitIntoSubTUs = (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422);
3252 uint32_t absPartIdxStep = cuGeom.numPartitions >> tuDepthC * 2;
3253 const Yuv* fencYuv = mode.fencYuv;
3254
3255 // code full block
3256 if (bCheckFull)
3257 {
3258 uint32_t trSizeC = 1 << log2TrSizeC;
3259 int partSize = partitionFromLog2Size(log2TrSize);
3260 int partSizeC = partitionFromLog2Size(log2TrSizeC);
3261 const uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
3262 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << (LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2);
3263 coeff_t* coeffCurY = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[0] + coeffOffsetY;
3264
3265 bool checkTransformSkip = m_slice->m_pps->bTransformSkipEnabled && !cu.m_tqBypass[0];
3266 bool checkTransformSkipY = checkTransformSkip && log2TrSize <= MAX_LOG2_TS_SIZE;
3267 bool checkTransformSkipC = checkTransformSkip && log2TrSizeC <= MAX_LOG2_TS_SIZE;

3645 primitives.cu[partSizeC].copy_ss(curResiC, strideResiC, m_tsResidual, trSizeC);
3646 }
3647
3648 cu.setCbfPartRange(cbfFlag[chromaId][tuIterator.section] << tuDepth, (TextType)chromaId, absPartIdxC, tuIterator.absPartIdxStep);
3649 }
3650 while (tuIterator.isNextSection());
3651 }
3652 }
3653
3654 // Here we were encoding cbfs and coefficients, after calculating distortion above.
3655 // Now I am encoding only cbfs, since I have encoded coefficients above. I have just collected
3656 // bits required for coefficients and added with number of cbf bits. As I tested the order does not
3657 // make any difference. But bit confused whether I should load the original context as below.
3658 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].rqtRoot);
3659 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
3660
3661 //Encode cbf flags
3662 if (codeChroma)
3663 {
3664 if (!splitIntoSubTUs)
3665 {
3666 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U][0], tuDepth);
3667 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V][0], tuDepth);
3668 }
3669 else
3670 {
3671 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
3672 offsetSubTUCBFs(cu, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, absPartIdx);
3673 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U][0], tuDepth);
3674 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U][1], tuDepth);
3675 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V][0], tuDepth);
3676 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V][1], tuDepth);
3677 }
3678 }
3679
3680 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfLuma(cbfFlag[TEXT_LUMA][0], tuDepth);
3681
3682 uint32_t cbfBits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
3683
3684 uint32_t coeffBits = 0;
3685 coeffBits = singleBits[TEXT_LUMA][0];
3686 for (uint32_t subTUIndex = 0; subTUIndex < 2; subTUIndex++)
3687 {
3688 coeffBits += singleBits[TEXT_CHROMA_U][subTUIndex];
3689 coeffBits += singleBits[TEXT_CHROMA_V][subTUIndex];
3690 }
3691
3692 // In split mode, we need only coeffBits. The reason is encoding chroma cbfs is different from luma.
3693 // In case of chroma, if any one of the split block's cbf is 1, then we need to encode cbf 1, and then for
3694 // four split block's individual cbf value. This is not known before analysis of four split blocks.
3695 // For that reason, I am collecting individual coefficient bits only.
3696 fullCost.bits = bSplitPresentFlag ? cbfBits + coeffBits : coeffBits;
3697
3698 fullCost.distortion += singleDist[TEXT_LUMA][0];
3699 fullCost.energy += singleEnergy[TEXT_LUMA][0];// need to check we need to add chroma also
3700 for (uint32_t subTUIndex = 0; subTUIndex < 2; subTUIndex++)
3701 {
3702 fullCost.distortion += singleDist[TEXT_CHROMA_U][subTUIndex];
3703 fullCost.distortion += singleDist[TEXT_CHROMA_V][subTUIndex];
3704 }
3705
3706 if (m_rdCost.m_psyRd)
3707 fullCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcPsyRdCost(fullCost.distortion, fullCost.bits, fullCost.energy);
3708 else if(m_rdCost.m_ssimRd)
3709 fullCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcSsimRdCost(fullCost.distortion, fullCost.bits, fullCost.energy);
3710 else
3711 fullCost.rdcost = m_rdCost.calcRdCost(fullCost.distortion, fullCost.bits);
3712
3713 if (m_param->limitTU && bCheckSplit)
3714 {
3715 // Stop recursion if the TU's energy level is minimal
3716 uint32_t numCoeff = trSize * trSize;
3717 if (cbfFlag[TEXT_LUMA][0] == 0)
3718 bCheckSplit = false;
3719 else if (numSig[TEXT_LUMA][0] < (numCoeff / 64))
3720 {
3721 uint32_t energy = 0;
3722 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numCoeff; i++)
3723 energy += abs(coeffCurY[i]);
3724 if (energy == numSig[TEXT_LUMA][0])
3725 bCheckSplit = false;
3726 }
3727 }
3728
3729 if (bSaveTUData)
3730 {
3731 for (int plane = 0; plane < MAX_NUM_COMPONENT; plane++)
3732 {
3733 for(int part = 0; part < (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422) + 1; part++)
3734 {
3735 m_cacheTU.bestTransformMode[idx][plane][part] = bestTransformMode[plane][part];
3736 m_cacheTU.cbfFlag[idx][plane][part] = cbfFlag[plane][part];
3737 }
3738 }
3739 m_cacheTU.cost[idx] = fullCost;
3740 m_entropyCoder.store(m_cacheTU.rqtStore[idx]);
3741 }
3742 }
3743 if (bLoadTUData)
3744 {
3745 for (int plane = 0; plane < MAX_NUM_COMPONENT; plane++)
3746 {
3747 for(int part = 0; part < (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422) + 1; part++)
3748 {
3749 bestTransformMode[plane][part] = m_cacheTU.bestTransformMode[idx][plane][part];
3750 cbfFlag[plane][part] = m_cacheTU.cbfFlag[idx][plane][part];
3751 }
3752 }
3753 fullCost = m_cacheTU.cost[idx];
3754 m_entropyCoder.load(m_cacheTU.rqtStore[idx]);
3755 bCheckFull = true;
3756 }
3757
3758 // code sub-blocks
3759 if (bCheckSplit)
3760 {
3761 if (bCheckFull)
3762 {
3763 m_entropyCoder.store(m_rqt[depth].rqtTest);
3764 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].rqtRoot);
3765 }
3766
3767 Cost splitCost;
3768 if (bSplitPresentFlag && (log2TrSize <= depthRange[1] && log2TrSize > depthRange[0]))
3769 {
3770 // Subdiv flag can be encoded at the start of analysis of split blocks.
3771 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
3772 m_entropyCoder.codeTransformSubdivFlag(1, 5 - log2TrSize);
3773 splitCost.bits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
3774 }
3775
3776 bool yCbCrCbf = splitTU(mode, cuGeom, absPartIdx, tuDepth, resiYuv, splitCost, depthRange, 0);
3777 if (yCbCrCbf || !bCheckFull)
3778 {
3779 if (splitCost.rdcost < fullCost.rdcost)
3780 {
3781 if (m_limitTU & X265_TU_LIMIT_BFS)
3782 {
3783 uint32_t nextlog2TrSize = cuGeom.log2CUSize - (tuDepth + 1);
3784 bool nextSplit = nextlog2TrSize > depthRange[0];
3785 if (nextSplit)
3786 {
3787 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].rqtRoot);
3788 splitCost.bits = splitCost.distortion = splitCost.rdcost = splitCost.energy = 0;
3789 if (bSplitPresentFlag && (log2TrSize <= depthRange[1] && log2TrSize > depthRange[0]))
3790 {
3791 // Subdiv flag can be encoded at the start of analysis of split blocks.
3792 m_entropyCoder.resetBits();
3793 m_entropyCoder.codeTransformSubdivFlag(1, 5 - log2TrSize);
3794 splitCost.bits = m_entropyCoder.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
3795 }
3796 splitTU(mode, cuGeom, absPartIdx, tuDepth, resiYuv, splitCost, depthRange, 1);
3797 }
3798 }
3799 outCosts.distortion += splitCost.distortion;
3800 outCosts.rdcost += splitCost.rdcost;
3801 outCosts.bits += splitCost.bits;
3802 outCosts.energy += splitCost.energy;
3803 return;
3804 }
3805 else
3806 outCosts.energy += splitCost.energy;
3807 }
3808
3809 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(bestTransformMode[TEXT_LUMA][0], TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, depth);
3810 if (codeChroma)
3811 {
3812 if (!splitIntoSubTUs)
3813 {
3814 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(bestTransformMode[TEXT_CHROMA_U][0], TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdx, depth);
3815 cu.setTransformSkipSubParts(bestTransformMode[TEXT_CHROMA_V][0], TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdx, depth);
3816 }
3817 else
3818 {
3819 uint32_t tuNumParts = absPartIdxStep >> 1;
3820 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(bestTransformMode[TEXT_CHROMA_U][0], TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdx , tuNumParts);
3821 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(bestTransformMode[TEXT_CHROMA_U][1], TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdx + tuNumParts, tuNumParts);
3822 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(bestTransformMode[TEXT_CHROMA_V][0], TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdx , tuNumParts);
3823 cu.setTransformSkipPartRange(bestTransformMode[TEXT_CHROMA_V][1], TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdx + tuNumParts, tuNumParts);
3824 }
3825 }
3826 X265_CHECK(bCheckFull, "check-full must be set\n");
3827 m_entropyCoder.load(m_rqt[depth].rqtTest);
3828 }
3829
3830 cu.setTUDepthSubParts(tuDepth, absPartIdx, depth);
3831 cu.setCbfSubParts(cbfFlag[TEXT_LUMA][0] << tuDepth, TEXT_LUMA, absPartIdx, depth);
3832
3833 if (codeChroma)
3834 {
3835 if (!splitIntoSubTUs)
3836 {
3837 cu.setCbfSubParts(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U][0] << tuDepth, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdx, depth);
3838 cu.setCbfSubParts(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V][0] << tuDepth, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdx, depth);
3839 }
3840 else
3841 {
3842 uint32_t tuNumParts = absPartIdxStep >> 1;
3843
3844 offsetCBFs(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U]);
3845 offsetCBFs(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V]);
3846 cu.setCbfPartRange(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U][0] << tuDepth, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdx , tuNumParts);
3847 cu.setCbfPartRange(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_U][1] << tuDepth, TEXT_CHROMA_U, absPartIdx + tuNumParts, tuNumParts);
3848 cu.setCbfPartRange(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V][0] << tuDepth, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdx , tuNumParts);
3849 cu.setCbfPartRange(cbfFlag[TEXT_CHROMA_V][1] << tuDepth, TEXT_CHROMA_V, absPartIdx + tuNumParts, tuNumParts);
3850 }
3851 }
3852
3853 outCosts.distortion += fullCost.distortion;
3854 outCosts.rdcost += fullCost.rdcost;
3855 outCosts.bits += fullCost.bits;
3856 outCosts.energy += fullCost.energy;
3857}

3859void Search::codeInterSubdivCbfQT(CUData& cu, uint32_t absPartIdx, const uint32_t tuDepth, const uint32_t depthRange[2])
3860{
3861 X265_CHECK(cu.isInter(absPartIdx), "codeInterSubdivCbfQT() with intra block\n");
3862
3863 const bool bSubdiv = tuDepth < cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx];
3864 uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
3865 if (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
3866 {
3867 if (!(log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift < 2))
3868 {
3869 uint32_t parentIdx = absPartIdx & (0xFF << (log2TrSize + 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2);
3870 if (!tuDepth || cu.getCbf(parentIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth - 1))
3871 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cu, absPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_U, tuDepth, !bSubdiv);
3872 if (!tuDepth || cu.getCbf(parentIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth - 1))
3873 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfChroma(cu, absPartIdx, TEXT_CHROMA_V, tuDepth, !bSubdiv);
3874 }
3875 }
3876
3877 if (!bSubdiv)
3878 {
3879 m_entropyCoder.codeQtCbfLuma(cu.getCbf(absPartIdx, TEXT_LUMA, tuDepth), tuDepth);
3880 }
3881 else
3882 {
3883 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize -1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
3884 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
3885 codeInterSubdivCbfQT(cu, absPartIdx, tuDepth + 1, depthRange);
3886 }
3887}

3889void Search::saveResidualQTData(CUData& cu, ShortYuv& resiYuv, uint32_t absPartIdx, uint32_t tuDepth)
3890{
3891 const uint32_t log2TrSize = cu.m_log2CUSize[0] - tuDepth;
3892
3893 if (tuDepth < cu.m_tuDepth[absPartIdx])
3894 {
3895 uint32_t qNumParts = 1 << (log2TrSize - 1 - LOG2_UNIT_SIZE) * 2;
3896 for (uint32_t qIdx = 0; qIdx < 4; ++qIdx, absPartIdx += qNumParts)
3897 saveResidualQTData(cu, resiYuv, absPartIdx, tuDepth + 1);
3898 return;
3899 }
3900
3901 const uint32_t qtLayer = log2TrSize - 2;
3902
3903 uint32_t log2TrSizeC = log2TrSize - m_hChromaShift;
3904 uint32_t codeChroma = (m_csp != X265_CSP_I400 && m_frame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400) ? 1 : 0;
3905 uint32_t tuDepthC = tuDepth;
3906 if (log2TrSizeC < 2)
3907 {
3908 X265_CHECK(log2TrSize == 2 && m_csp != X265_CSP_I444 && tuDepth, "invalid tuDepth\n");
3909 log2TrSizeC = 2;
3910 tuDepthC--;
3911 codeChroma &= !(absPartIdx & 3);
3912 }
3913
3914 m_rqt[qtLayer].resiQtYuv.copyPartToPartLuma(resiYuv, absPartIdx, log2TrSize);
3915
3916 uint32_t numCoeffY = 1 << (log2TrSize * 2);
3917 uint32_t coeffOffsetY = absPartIdx << LOG2_UNIT_SIZE * 2;
3918 coeff_t* coeffSrcY = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[0] + coeffOffsetY;
3919 coeff_t* coeffDstY = cu.m_trCoeff[0] + coeffOffsetY;
3920 memcpy(coeffDstY, coeffSrcY, sizeof(coeff_t) * numCoeffY);
3921
3922 if (codeChroma)
3923 {
3924 m_rqt[qtLayer].resiQtYuv.copyPartToPartChroma(resiYuv, absPartIdx, log2TrSizeC + m_hChromaShift);
3925
3926 uint32_t numCoeffC = 1 << (log2TrSizeC * 2 + (m_csp == X265_CSP_I422));
3927 uint32_t coeffOffsetC = coeffOffsetY >> (m_hChromaShift + m_vChromaShift);
3928
3929 coeff_t* coeffSrcU = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[1] + coeffOffsetC;
3930 coeff_t* coeffSrcV = m_rqt[qtLayer].coeffRQT[2] + coeffOffsetC;
3931 coeff_t* coeffDstU = cu.m_trCoeff[1] + coeffOffsetC;
3932 coeff_t* coeffDstV = cu.m_trCoeff[2] + coeffOffsetC;
3933 memcpy(coeffDstU, coeffSrcU, sizeof(coeff_t) * numCoeffC);
3934 memcpy(coeffDstV, coeffSrcV, sizeof(coeff_t) * numCoeffC);
3935 }

3951/* swap the current mode/cost with the mode with the highest cost in the
3952 * current candidate list, if its cost is better (maintain a top N list) */
3953void Search::updateCandList(uint32_t mode, uint64_t cost, int maxCandCount, uint32_t* candModeList, uint64_t* candCostList)
3954{
3955 uint32_t maxIndex = 0;
3956 uint64_t maxValue = 0;
3957
3958 for (int i = 0; i < maxCandCount; i++)
3959 {
3960 if (maxValue < candCostList[i])
3961 {
3962 maxValue = candCostList[i];
3963 maxIndex = i;
3964 }
3965 }
3966
3967 if (cost < maxValue)
3968 {
3969 candCostList[maxIndex] = cost;
3970 candModeList[maxIndex] = mode;
3971 }

3974void Search::checkDQP(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
3975{
3976 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
3977 if (cu.m_slice->m_pps->bUseDQP && cuGeom.depth <= cu.m_slice->m_pps->maxCuDQPDepth)
3978 {
3979 if (cu.getQtRootCbf(0))
3980 {
3981 if (m_param->rdLevel >= 3)
3982 {
3983 mode.contexts.resetBits();
3984 mode.contexts.codeDeltaQP(cu, 0);
3985 uint32_t bits = mode.contexts.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
3986 mode.totalBits += bits;
3987 updateModeCost(mode);
3988 }
3989 else if (m_param->rdLevel <= 1)
3990 {
3991 mode.sa8dBits++;
3992 mode.sa8dCost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost((uint32_t)mode.distortion, mode.sa8dBits);
3993 }
3994 else
3995 {
3996 mode.totalBits++;
3997 updateModeCost(mode);
3998 }
3999 }
4000 else
4001 cu.setQPSubParts(cu.getRefQP(0), 0, cuGeom.depth);
4002 }

4005void Search::checkDQPForSplitPred(Mode& mode, const CUGeom& cuGeom)
4006{
4007 CUData& cu = mode.cu;
4008
4009 if ((cuGeom.depth == cu.m_slice->m_pps->maxCuDQPDepth) && cu.m_slice->m_pps->bUseDQP)
4010 {
4011 bool hasResidual = false;
4012
4013 /* Check if any sub-CU has a non-zero QP */
4014 for (uint32_t blkIdx = 0; blkIdx < cuGeom.numPartitions; blkIdx++)
4015 {
4016 if (cu.getQtRootCbf(blkIdx))
4017 {
4018 hasResidual = true;
4019 break;
4020 }
4021 }
4022 if (hasResidual)
4023 {
4024 if (m_param->rdLevel >= 3)
4025 {
4026 mode.contexts.resetBits();
4027 mode.contexts.codeDeltaQP(cu, 0);
4028 uint32_t bits = mode.contexts.getNumberOfWrittenBits();
4029 mode.totalBits += bits;
4030 updateModeCost(mode);
4031 }
4032 else if (m_param->rdLevel <= 1)
4033 {
4034 mode.sa8dBits++;
4035 mode.sa8dCost = m_rdCost.calcRdSADCost((uint32_t)mode.distortion, mode.sa8dBits);
4036 }
4037 else
4038 {
4039 mode.totalBits++;
4040 updateModeCost(mode);
4041 }
4042 /* For all zero CBF sub-CUs, reset QP to RefQP (so that deltaQP is not signalled).
4043 When the non-zero CBF sub-CU is found, stop */
4044 cu.setQPSubCUs(cu.getRefQP(0), 0, cuGeom.depth);
4045 }
4046 else
4047 /* No residual within this CU or subCU, so reset QP to RefQP */
4048 cu.setQPSubParts(cu.getRefQP(0), 0, cuGeom.depth);
4049 }
